 16 (function( window, undefined ) {

 18 // Use the correct document accordingly with window argument (sandbox)
 19 var document = window.document,
 20 	navigator = window.navigator,
 21 	location = window.location;
 22 var jQuery = (function() {
 23 
 24 // Define a local copy of jQuery
 25 var jQuery = function( selector, context ) {
 26 		// The jQuery object is actually just the init constructor 'enhanced'
 27 		return new jQuery.fn.init( selector, context, rootjQuery );
 28 	},
 29 
 30 	// Map over jQuery in case of overwrite
 31 	_jQuery = window.jQuery,
 32 
 33 	// Map over the $ in case of overwrite
 34 	_$ = window.$,
 35 
 36 	// A central reference to the root jQuery(document)
 37 	rootjQuery,
 38 
 39 	// A simple way to check for HTML strings or ID strings
 40 	// (both of which we optimize for)
 41 	quickExpr = /^(?:[^<]*(<[\w\W]+>)[^>]*$|#([\w\-]*)$)/,
 42 
 43 	// Check if a string has a non-whitespace character in it
 44 	rnotwhite = /\S/,
 45 
 46 	// Used for trimming whitespace
 47 	trimLeft = /^\s+/,
 48 	trimRight = /\s+$/,
 49 
 50 	// Check for digits
 51 	rdigit = /\d/,
 52 
 53 	// Match a standalone tag
 54 	rsingleTag = /^<(\w+)\s*\/?>(?:<\/\1>)?$/,
 55 
 56 	// JSON RegExp
 57 	rvalidchars = /^[\],:{}\s]*$/,
 58 	rvalidescape = /\\(?:["\\\/bfnrt]|u[0-9a-fA-F]{4})/g,
 59 	rvalidtokens = /"[^"\\\n\r]*"|true|false|null|-?\d+(?:\.\d*)?(?:[eE][+\-]?\d+)?/g,
 60 	rvalidbraces = /(?:^|:|,)(?:\s*\[)+/g,
 61 
 62 	// Useragent RegExp
 63 	rwebkit = /(webkit)[ \/]([\w.]+)/,
 64 	ropera = /(opera)(?:.*version)?[ \/]([\w.]+)/,
 65 	rmsie = /(msie) ([\w.]+)/,
 66 	rmozilla = /(mozilla)(?:.*? rv:([\w.]+))?/,
 67 
 68 	// Keep a UserAgent string for use with jQuery.browser
 69 	userAgent = navigator.userAgent,
 70 
 71 	// For matching the engine and version of the browser
 72 	browserMatch,
 73 
 74 	// The deferred used on DOM ready
 75 	readyList,
 76 
 77 	// The ready event handler
 78 	DOMContentLoaded,
 79 
 80 	// Save a reference to some core methods
 81 	toString = Object.prototype.toString,
 82 	hasOwn = Object.prototype.hasOwnProperty,
 83 	push = Array.prototype.push,
 84 	slice = Array.prototype.slice,
 85 	trim = String.prototype.trim,
 86 	indexOf = Array.prototype.indexOf,
 87 
 88 	// [[Class]] -> type pairs
 89 	class2type = {};
 90 
 91 jQuery.fn = jQuery.prototype = {
 92 	constructor: jQuery,
 93 	init: function( selector, context, rootjQuery ) {
 94 		var match, elem, ret, doc;
 95 
 96 		// Handle $(""), $(null), or $(undefined)
 97 		if ( !selector ) {
 98 			return this;
 99 		}
100 
101 		// Handle $(DOMElement)
102 		if ( selector.nodeType ) {
103 			this.context = this[0] = selector;
104 			this.length = 1;
105 			return this;
106 		}
107 
108 		// The body element only exists once, optimize finding it
109 		if ( selector === "body" && !context && document.body ) {
110 			this.context = document;
111 			this[0] = document.body;
112 			this.selector = selector;
113 			this.length = 1;
114 			return this;
115 		}
116 
117 		// Handle HTML strings
118 		if ( typeof selector === "string" ) {
119 			// Are we dealing with HTML string or an ID?
120 			if ( selector.charAt(0) === "<" && selector.charAt( selector.length - 1 ) === ">" && selector.length >= 3 ) {
121 				// Assume that strings that start and end with <> are HTML and skip the regex check
122 				match = [ null, selector, null ];
123 
124 			} else {
125 				match = quickExpr.exec( selector );
126 			}
127 
128 			// Verify a match, and that no context was specified for #id
129 			if ( match && (match[1] || !context) ) {
130 
131 				// HANDLE: $(html) -> $(array)
132 				if ( match[1] ) {
133 					context = context instanceof jQuery ? context[0] : context;
134 					doc = (context ? context.ownerDocument || context : document);
135 
136 					// If a single string is passed in and it's a single tag
137 					// just do a createElement and skip the rest
138 					ret = rsingleTag.exec( selector );
139 
140 					if ( ret ) {
141 						if ( jQuery.isPlainObject( context ) ) {
142 							selector = [ document.createElement( ret[1] ) ];
143 							jQuery.fn.attr.call( selector, context, true );
144 
145 						} else {
146 							selector = [ doc.createElement( ret[1] ) ];
147 						}
148 
149 					} else {
150 						ret = jQuery.buildFragment( [ match[1] ], [ doc ] );
151 						selector = (ret.cacheable ? jQuery.clone(ret.fragment) : ret.fragment).childNodes;
152 					}
153 
154 					return jQuery.merge( this, selector );
155 
156 				// HANDLE: $("#id")
157 				} else {
158 					elem = document.getElementById( match[2] );
159 
160 					// Check parentNode to catch when Blackberry 4.6 returns
161 					// nodes that are no longer in the document #6963
162 					if ( elem && elem.parentNode ) {
163 						// Handle the case where IE and Opera return items
164 						// by name instead of ID
165 						if ( elem.id !== match[2] ) {
166 							return rootjQuery.find( selector );
167 						}
168 
169 						// Otherwise, we inject the element directly into the jQuery object
170 						this.length = 1;
171 						this[0] = elem;
172 					}
173 
174 					this.context = document;
175 					this.selector = selector;
176 					return this;
177 				}
178 
179 			// HANDLE: $(expr, $(...))
180 			} else if ( !context || context.jquery ) {
181 				return (context || rootjQuery).find( selector );
182 
183 			// HANDLE: $(expr, context)
184 			// (which is just equivalent to: $(context).find(expr)
185 			} else {
186 				return this.constructor( context ).find( selector );
187 			}
188 
189 		// HANDLE: $(function)
190 		// Shortcut for document ready
191 		} else if ( jQuery.isFunction( selector ) ) {
192 			return rootjQuery.ready( selector );
193 		}
194 
195 		if (selector.selector !== undefined) {
196 			this.selector = selector.selector;
197 			this.context = selector.context;
198 		}
199 
200 		return jQuery.makeArray( selector, this );
201 	},
202 
203 	// Start with an empty selector
204 	selector: "",
205 
206 	// The current version of jQuery being used
207 	jquery: "1.6.1",
208 
209 	// The default length of a jQuery object is 0
210 	length: 0,
211 
212 	// The number of elements contained in the matched element set
213 	size: function() {
214 		return this.length;
215 	},
216 
217 	toArray: function() {
218 		return slice.call( this, 0 );
219 	},
220 
221 	// Get the Nth element in the matched element set OR
222 	// Get the whole matched element set as a clean array
223 	get: function( num ) {
224 		return num == null ?
225 
226 			// Return a 'clean' array
227 			this.toArray() :
228 
229 			// Return just the object
230 			( num < 0 ? this[ this.length + num ] : this[ num ] );
231 	},
232 
233 	// Take an array of elements and push it onto the stack
234 	// (returning the new matched element set)
235 	pushStack: function( elems, name, selector ) {
236 		// Build a new jQuery matched element set
237 		var ret = this.constructor();
238 
239 		if ( jQuery.isArray( elems ) ) {
240 			push.apply( ret, elems );
241 
242 		} else {
243 			jQuery.merge( ret, elems );
244 		}
245 
246 		// Add the old object onto the stack (as a reference)
247 		ret.prevObject = this;
248 
249 		ret.context = this.context;
250 
251 		if ( name === "find" ) {
252 			ret.selector = this.selector + (this.selector ? " " : "") + selector;
253 		} else if ( name ) {
254 			ret.selector = this.selector + "." + name + "(" + selector + ")";
255 		}
256 
257 		// Return the newly-formed element set
258 		return ret;
259 	},
260 
261 	// Execute a callback for every element in the matched set.
262 	// (You can seed the arguments with an array of args, but this is
263 	// only used internally.)
264 	each: function( callback, args ) {
265 		return jQuery.each( this, callback, args );
266 	},
267 
268 	ready: function( fn ) {
269 		// Attach the listeners
270 		jQuery.bindReady();
271 
272 		// Add the callback
273 		readyList.done( fn );
274 
275 		return this;
276 	},
277 
278 	eq: function( i ) {
279 		return i === -1 ?
280 			this.slice( i ) :
281 282 			this.slice( i, +i + 1 );
283 	},
284 
285 	first: function() {
286 		return this.eq( 0 );
287 	},
288 
289 	last: function() {
290 		return this.eq( -1 );
291 	},
292 
293 	slice: function() {
294 		return this.pushStack( slice.apply( this, arguments ),
295 			"slice", slice.call(arguments).join(",") );
296 	},
297 
298 	map: function( callback ) {
299 		return this.pushStack( jQuery.map(this, function( elem, i ) {
300 			return callback.call( elem, i, elem );
301 		}));
302 	},
303 
304 	end: function() {
305 		return this.prevObject || this.constructor(null);
306 	},
307 
308 	// For internal use only.
309 	// Behaves like an Array's method, not like a jQuery method.
310 	push: push,
311 	sort: [].sort,
312 	splice: [].splice
313 };
314 
315 // Give the init function the jQuery prototype for later instantiation
316 jQuery.fn.init.prototype = jQuery.fn;
317 
318 jQuery.extend = jQuery.fn.extend = function() {
319 	var options, name, src, copy, copyIsArray, clone,
320 		target = arguments[0] || {},
321 		i = 1,
322 		length = arguments.length,
323 		deep = false;
324 
325 	// Handle a deep copy situation
326 	if ( typeof target === "boolean" ) {
327 		deep = target;
328 		target = arguments[1] || {};
329 		// skip the boolean and the target
330 		i = 2;
331 	}
332 
333 	// Handle case when target is a string or something (possible in deep copy)
334 	if ( typeof target !== "object" && !jQuery.isFunction(target) ) {
335 		target = {};
336 	}
337 
338 	// extend jQuery itself if only one argument is passed
339 	if ( length === i ) {
340 		target = this;
341 		--i;
342 	}
343 
344 	for ( ; i < length; i++ ) {
345 		// Only deal with non-null/undefined values
346 		if ( (options = arguments[ i ]) != null ) {
347 			// Extend the base object
348 			for ( name in options ) {
349 				src = target[ name ];
350 				copy = options[ name ];
351 
352 				// Prevent never-ending loop
353 				if ( target === copy ) {
354 					continue;
355 				}
356 
357 				// Recurse if we're merging plain objects or arrays
358 				if ( deep && copy && ( jQuery.isPlainObject(copy) || (copyIsArray = jQuery.isArray(copy)) ) ) {
359 					if ( copyIsArray ) {
360 						copyIsArray = false;
361 						clone = src && jQuery.isArray(src) ? src : [];
362 
363 					} else {
364 						clone = src && jQuery.isPlainObject(src) ? src : {};
365 					}
366 
367 					// Never move original objects, clone them
368 					target[ name ] = jQuery.extend( deep, clone, copy );
369 
370 				// Don't bring in undefined values
371 				} else if ( copy !== undefined ) {
372 					target[ name ] = copy;
373 				}
374 			}
375 		}
376 377 	}
378 
379 	// Return the modified object
380 	return target;
381 };
382 
383 jQuery.extend({
384 	noConflict: function( deep ) {
385 		if ( window.$ === jQuery ) {
386 			window.$ = _$;
387 		}
388 
389 		if ( deep && window.jQuery === jQuery ) {
390 			window.jQuery = _jQuery;
391 		}
392 
393 		return jQuery;
394 	},
395 
396 	// Is the DOM ready to be used? Set to true once it occurs.
397 	isReady: false,
398 
399 	// A counter to track how many items to wait for before
400 	// the ready event fires. See #6781
401 	readyWait: 1,
402 
403 	// Hold (or release) the ready event
404 	holdReady: function( hold ) {
405 		if ( hold ) {
406 			jQuery.readyWait++;
407 		} else {
408 			jQuery.ready( true );
409 		}
410 	},
411 
412 	// Handle when the DOM is ready
413 	ready: function( wait ) {
414 		// Either a released hold or an DOMready/load event and not yet ready
415 		if ( (wait === true && !--jQuery.readyWait) || (wait !== true && !jQuery.isReady) ) {
416 			// Make sure body exists, at least, in case IE gets a little overzealous (ticket #5443).
417 			if ( !document.body ) {
418 				return setTimeout( jQuery.ready, 1 );
419 			}
420 
421 			// Remember that the DOM is ready
422 			jQuery.isReady = true;
423 
424 			// If a normal DOM Ready event fired, decrement, and wait if need be
425 			if ( wait !== true && --jQuery.readyWait > 0 ) {
426 				return;
427 			}
428 
429 			// If there are functions bound, to execute
430 			readyList.resolveWith( document, [ jQuery ] );
431 
432 			// Trigger any bound ready events
433 			if ( jQuery.fn.trigger ) {
434 				jQuery( document ).trigger( "ready" ).unbind( "ready" );
435 			}
436 		}
437 	},
438 
439 	bindReady: function() {
440 		if ( readyList ) {
441 			return;
442 		}
443 
444 		readyList = jQuery._Deferred();
445 
446 		// Catch cases where $(document).ready() is called after the
447 		// browser event has already occurred.
448 		if ( document.readyState === "complete" ) {
449 			// Handle it asynchronously to allow scripts the opportunity to delay ready
450 			return setTimeout( jQuery.ready, 1 );
451 		}
452 
453 		// Mozilla, Opera and webkit nightlies currently support this event
454 		if ( document.addEventListener ) {
455 			// Use the handy event callback
456 			document.addEventListener( "DOMContentLoaded", DOMContentLoaded, false );
457 
458 			// A fallback to window.onload, that will always work
459 			window.addEventListener( "load", jQuery.ready, false );
460 
461 		// If IE event model is used
462 		} else if ( document.attachEvent ) {
463 			// ensure firing before onload,
464 			// maybe late but safe also for iframes
465 			document.attachEvent( "onreadystatechange", DOMContentLoaded );
466 
467 			// A fallback to window.onload, that will always work
468 			window.attachEvent( "onload", jQuery.ready );
469 
470 			// If IE and not a frame
471 			// continually check to see if the document is ready
472 			var toplevel = false;
473 
474 			try {
475 				toplevel = window.frameElement == null;
476 			} catch(e) {}
477 
478 			if ( document.documentElement.doScroll && toplevel ) {
479 				doScrollCheck();
480 			}
481 		}
482 	},
483 
484 	// See test/unit/core.js for details concerning isFunction.
485 	// Since version 1.3, DOM methods and functions like alert
486 	// aren't supported. They return false on IE (#2968).
487 	isFunction: function( obj ) {
488 		return jQuery.type(obj) === "function";
489 	},
490 
491 	isArray: Array.isArray || function( obj ) {
492 		return jQuery.type(obj) === "array";
493 	},
494 
495 	// A crude way of determining if an object is a window
496 	isWindow: function( obj ) {
497 		return obj && typeof obj === "object" && "setInterval" in obj;
498 	},
499 
500 	isNaN: function( obj ) {
501 		return obj == null || !rdigit.test( obj ) || isNaN( obj );
502 	},
503 
504 	type: function( obj ) {
505 		return obj == null ?
506 			String( obj ) :
507 			class2type[ toString.call(obj) ] || "object";
508 	},
509 
510 	isPlainObject: function( obj ) {
511 		// Must be an Object.
512 		// Because of IE, we also have to check the presence of the constructor property.
513 		// Make sure that DOM nodes and window objects don't pass through, as well
514 		if ( !obj || jQuery.type(obj) !== "object" || obj.nodeType || jQuery.isWindow( obj ) ) {
515 			return false;
516 		}
517 
518 		// Not own constructor property must be Object
519 		if ( obj.constructor &&
520 			!hasOwn.call(obj, "constructor") &&
521 			!hasOwn.call(obj.constructor.prototype, "isPrototypeOf") ) {
522 			return false;
523 		}
524 
525 		// Own properties are enumerated firstly, so to speed up,
526 		// if last one is own, then all properties are own.
527 
528 		var key;
529 		for ( key in obj ) {}
530 
531 		return key === undefined || hasOwn.call( obj, key );
532 	},
533 
534 	isEmptyObject: function( obj ) {
535 		for ( var name in obj ) {
536 			return false;
537 		}
538 		return true;
539 	},
540 
541 	error: function( msg ) {
542 		throw msg;
543 	},
544 
545 	parseJSON: function( data ) {
546 		if ( typeof data !== "string" || !data ) {
547 			return null;
548 		}
549 
550 		// Make sure leading/trailing whitespace is removed (IE can't handle it)
551 		data = jQuery.trim( data );
552 
553 		// Attempt to parse using the native JSON parser first
554 		if ( window.JSON && window.JSON.parse ) {
555 			return window.JSON.parse( data );
556 		}
557 
558 		// Make sure the incoming data is actual JSON
559 		// Logic borrowed from http://json.org/json2.js
560 		if ( rvalidchars.test( data.replace( rvalidescape, "@" )
561 			.replace( rvalidtokens, "]" )
562 			.replace( rvalidbraces, "")) ) {
563 
564 			return (new Function( "return " + data ))();
565 
566 		}
567 		jQuery.error( "Invalid JSON: " + data );
568 	},
569 
570 	// Cross-browser xml parsing
571 	// (xml & tmp used internally)
572 	parseXML: function( data , xml , tmp ) {
573 
574 		if ( window.DOMParser ) { // Standard
575 			tmp = new DOMParser();
576 			xml = tmp.parseFromString( data , "text/xml" );
577 		} else { // IE
578 			xml = new ActiveXObject( "Microsoft.XMLDOM" );
579 			xml.async = "false";
580 			xml.loadXML( data );
581 		}
582 
583 		tmp = xml.documentElement;
584 
585 		if ( ! tmp || ! tmp.nodeName || tmp.nodeName === "parsererror" ) {
586 			jQuery.error( "Invalid XML: " + data );
587 		}
588 
589 		return xml;
590 	},
591 
592 	noop: function() {},
593 
594 	// Evaluates a script in a global context
595 	// Workarounds based on findings by Jim Driscoll
596 	// http://weblogs.java.net/blog/driscoll/archive/2009/09/08/eval-javascript-global-context
597 	globalEval: function( data ) {
598 		if ( data && rnotwhite.test( data ) ) {
599 			// We use execScript on Internet Explorer
600 			// We use an anonymous function so that context is window
601 			// rather than jQuery in Firefox
602 			( window.execScript || function( data ) {
603 				window[ "eval" ].call( window, data );
604 			} )( data );
605 		}
606 	},
607 
608 	nodeName: function( elem, name ) {
609 		return elem.nodeName && elem.nodeName.toUpperCase() === name.toUpperCase();
610 	},
611 
612 	// args is for internal usage only
613 	each: function( object, callback, args ) {
614 		var name, i = 0,
615 			length = object.length,
616 			isObj = length === undefined || jQuery.isFunction( object );
617 
618 		if ( args ) {
619 			if ( isObj ) {
620 				for ( name in object ) {
621 					if ( callback.apply( object[ name ], args ) === false ) {
622 						break;
623 					}
624 				}
625 			} else {
626 				for ( ; i < length; ) {
627 					if ( callback.apply( object[ i++ ], args ) === false ) {
628 						break;
629 					}
630 				}
631 			}
632 
633 		// A special, fast, case for the most common use of each
634 		} else {
635 			if ( isObj ) {
636 637 				for ( name in object ) {
638 					if ( callback.call( object[ name ], name, object[ name ] ) === false ) {
639 						break;
640 					}
641 				}
642 			} else {
643 				for ( ; i < length; ) {
644 					if ( callback.call( object[ i ], i, object[ i++ ] ) === false ) {
645 						break;
646 					}
647 				}
648 			}
649 		}
650 
651 		return object;
652 	},
653 
654 	// Use native String.trim function wherever possible
655 	trim: trim ?
656 		function( text ) {
657 			return text == null ?
658 				"" :
659 				trim.call( text );
660 		} :
661 
662 		// Otherwise use our own trimming functionality
663 		function( text ) {
664 			return text == null ?
665 				"" :
666 				text.toString().replace( trimLeft, "" ).replace( trimRight, "" );
667 		},
668 
669 	// results is for internal usage only
670 	makeArray: function( array, results ) {
671 		var ret = results || [];
672 
673 		if ( array != null ) {
674 			// The window, strings (and functions) also have 'length'
675 			// The extra typeof function check is to prevent crashes
676 			// in Safari 2 (See: #3039)
677 			// Tweaked logic slightly to handle Blackberry 4.7 RegExp issues #6930
678 			var type = jQuery.type( array );
679 
680 			if ( array.length == null || type === "string" || type === "function" || type === "regexp" || jQuery.isWindow( array ) ) {
681 				push.call( ret, array );
682 			} else {
683 				jQuery.merge( ret, array );
684 			}
685 		}
686 
687 		return ret;
688 	},
689 
690 	inArray: function( elem, array ) {
691 
692 		if ( indexOf ) {
693 			return indexOf.call( array, elem );
694 		}
695 
696 		for ( var i = 0, length = array.length; i < length; i++ ) {
697 			if ( array[ i ] === elem ) {
698 				return i;
699 			}
700 		}
701 
702 		return -1;
703 	},
704 
705 	merge: function( first, second ) {
706 		var i = first.length,
707 			j = 0;
708 
709 		if ( typeof second.length === "number" ) {
710 			for ( var l = second.length; j < l; j++ ) {
711 				first[ i++ ] = second[ j ];
712 			}
713 
714 		} else {
715 			while ( second[j] !== undefined ) {
716 				first[ i++ ] = second[ j++ ];
717 			}
718 		}
719 
720 		first.length = i;
721 
722 		return first;
723 	},
724 
725 	grep: function( elems, callback, inv ) {
726 		var ret = [], retVal;
727 		inv = !!inv;
728 
729 		// Go through the array, only saving the items
730 		// that pass the validator function
731 		for ( var i = 0, length = elems.length; i < length; i++ ) {
732 			retVal = !!callback( elems[ i ], i );
733 			if ( inv !== retVal ) {
734 				ret.push( elems[ i ] );
735 			}
736 		}
737 
738 		return ret;
739 	},
740 
741 	// arg is for internal usage only
742 	map: function( elems, callback, arg ) {
743 		var value, key, ret = [],
744 			i = 0,
745 			length = elems.length,
746 			// jquery objects are treated as arrays
747 			isArray = elems instanceof jQuery || length !== undefined && typeof length === "number" && ( ( length > 0 && elems[ 0 ] && elems[ length -1 ] ) || length === 0 || jQuery.isArray( elems ) ) ;
748 
749 		// Go through the array, translating each of the items to their
750 		if ( isArray ) {
751 			for ( ; i < length; i++ ) {
752 				value = callback( elems[ i ], i, arg );
753 
754 				if ( value != null ) {
755 					ret[ ret.length ] = value;
756 				}
757 			}
758 
759 		// Go through every key on the object,
760 		} else {
761 			for ( key in elems ) {
762 				value = callback( elems[ key ], key, arg );
763 
764 				if ( value != null ) {
765 					ret[ ret.length ] = value;
766 				}
767 			}
768 		}
769 
770 		// Flatten any nested arrays
771 		return ret.concat.apply( [], ret );
772 	},
773 
774 	// A global GUID counter for objects
775 	guid: 1,
776 
777 	// Bind a function to a context, optionally partially applying any
778 	// arguments.
779 	proxy: function( fn, context ) {
780 		if ( typeof context === "string" ) {
781 			var tmp = fn[ context ];
782 			context = fn;
783 			fn = tmp;
784 		}
785 
786 		// Quick check to determine if target is callable, in the spec
787 		// this throws a TypeError, but we will just return undefined.
788 		if ( !jQuery.isFunction( fn ) ) {
789 			return undefined;
790 		}
791 
792 		// Simulated bind
793 		var args = slice.call( arguments, 2 ),
794 			proxy = function() {
795 				return fn.apply( context, args.concat( slice.call( arguments ) ) );
796 			};
797 
798 		// Set the guid of unique handler to the same of original handler, so it can be removed
799 		proxy.guid = fn.guid = fn.guid || proxy.guid || jQuery.guid++;
800 
801 		return proxy;
802 	},
803 
804 	// Mutifunctional method to get and set values to a collection
805 	// The value/s can be optionally by executed if its a function
806 	access: function( elems, key, value, exec, fn, pass ) {
807 		var length = elems.length;
808 
809 		// Setting many attributes
810 		if ( typeof key === "object" ) {
811 			for ( var k in key ) {
812 				jQuery.access( elems, k, key[k], exec, fn, value );
813 			}
814 			return elems;
815 		}
816 
817 		// Setting one attribute
818 		if ( value !== undefined ) {
819 			// Optionally, function values get executed if exec is true
820 			exec = !pass && exec && jQuery.isFunction(value);
821 
822 			for ( var i = 0; i < length; i++ ) {
823 				fn( elems[i], key, exec ? value.call( elems[i], i, fn( elems[i], key ) ) : value, pass );
824 			}
825 
826 			return elems;
827 		}
828 
829 		// Getting an attribute
830 		return length ? fn( elems[0], key ) : undefined;
831 	},
832 
833 	now: function() {
834 		return (new Date()).getTime();
835 	},

839 	uaMatch: function( ua ) {
840 		ua = ua.toLowerCase();
841 
842 		var match = rwebkit.exec( ua ) ||
843 			ropera.exec( ua ) ||
844 			rmsie.exec( ua ) ||
845 			ua.indexOf("compatible") < 0 && rmozilla.exec( ua ) ||
846 			[];
847 
848 		return { browser: match[1] || "", version: match[2] || "0" };
849 	},

851 	sub: function() {
852 		function jQuerySub( selector, context ) {
853 			return new jQuerySub.fn.init( selector, context );
854 		}
855 		jQuery.extend( true, jQuerySub, this );
856 		jQuerySub.superclass = this;
857 		jQuerySub.fn = jQuerySub.prototype = this();
858 		jQuerySub.fn.constructor = jQuerySub;
859 		jQuerySub.sub = this.sub;
860 		jQuerySub.fn.init = function init( selector, context ) {
861 			if ( context && context instanceof jQuery && !(context instanceof jQuerySub) ) {
862 				context = jQuerySub( context );
863 			}
864 
865 			return jQuery.fn.init.call( this, selector, context, rootjQuerySub );
866 		};
867 		jQuerySub.fn.init.prototype = jQuerySub.fn;
868 		var rootjQuerySub = jQuerySub(document);
869 		return jQuerySub;
870 	},

941 
942 var // Promise methods
943 	promiseMethods = "done fail isResolved isRejected promise then always pipe".split( " " ),
944 	// Static reference to slice
945 	sliceDeferred = [].slice;
946 
947 jQuery.extend({
948 	// Create a simple deferred (one callbacks list)
949 	_Deferred: function() {
950 		var // callbacks list
951 			callbacks = [],
952 			// stored [ context , args ]
953 			fired,
954 			// to avoid firing when already doing so
955 			firing,
956 			// flag to know if the deferred has been cancelled
957 			cancelled,
958 			// the deferred itself
959 			deferred  = {
960 
961 				// done( f1, f2, ...)
962 				done: function() {
963 					if ( !cancelled ) {
964 						var args = arguments,
965 							i,
966 							length,
967 							elem,
968 							type,
969 							_fired;
970 						if ( fired ) {
971 							_fired = fired;
972 							fired = 0;
973 						}
974 						for ( i = 0, length = args.length; i < length; i++ ) {
975 							elem = args[ i ];
976 							type = jQuery.type( elem );
977 							if ( type === "array" ) {
978 								deferred.done.apply( deferred, elem );
979 							} else if ( type === "function" ) {
980 								callbacks.push( elem );
981 							}
982 						}
983 						if ( _fired ) {
984 							deferred.resolveWith( _fired[ 0 ], _fired[ 1 ] );
985 						}
986 					}
987 					return this;
988 				},
989 
990 				// resolve with given context and args
991 				resolveWith: function( context, args ) {
992 					if ( !cancelled && !fired && !firing ) {
993 						// make sure args are available (#8421)
994 						args = args || [];
995 						firing = 1;
996 						try {
997 							while( callbacks[ 0 ] ) {
998 								callbacks.shift().apply( context, args );
999 							}
1000 						}
1001 						finally {
1002 							fired = [ context, args ];
1003 							firing = 0;
1004 						}
1005 					}
1006 					return this;
1007 				},
1008 
1009 				// resolve with this as context and given arguments
1010 				resolve: function() {
1011 					deferred.resolveWith( this, arguments );
1012 					return this;
1013 				},
1014 
1015 				// Has this deferred been resolved?
1016 				isResolved: function() {
1017 					return !!( firing || fired );
1018 				},
1019 
1020 				// Cancel
1021 				cancel: function() {
1022 					cancelled = 1;
1023 					callbacks = [];
1024 					return this;
1025 				}
1026 			};
1027 
1028 		return deferred;
1029 	},
1030 
1031 	// Full fledged deferred (two callbacks list)
1032 	Deferred: function( func ) {
1033 		var deferred = jQuery._Deferred(),
1034 			failDeferred = jQuery._Deferred(),
1035 			promise;
1036 		// Add errorDeferred methods, then and promise
1037 		jQuery.extend( deferred, {
1038 			then: function( doneCallbacks, failCallbacks ) {
1039 				deferred.done( doneCallbacks ).fail( failCallbacks );
1040 				return this;
1041 			},
1042 			always: function() {
1043 				return deferred.done.apply( deferred, arguments ).fail.apply( this, arguments );
1044 			},
1045 			fail: failDeferred.done,
1046 			rejectWith: failDeferred.resolveWith,
1047 			reject: failDeferred.resolve,
1048 			isRejected: failDeferred.isResolved,
1049 			pipe: function( fnDone, fnFail ) {
1050 				return jQuery.Deferred(function( newDefer ) {
1051 					jQuery.each( {
1052 						done: [ fnDone, "resolve" ],
1053 						fail: [ fnFail, "reject" ]
1054 					}, function( handler, data ) {
1055 						var fn = data[ 0 ],
1056 							action = data[ 1 ],
1057 							returned;
1058 						if ( jQuery.isFunction( fn ) ) {
1059 							deferred[ handler ](function() {
1060 								returned = fn.apply( this, arguments );
1061 								if ( returned && jQuery.isFunction( returned.promise ) ) {
1062 									returned.promise().then( newDefer.resolve, newDefer.reject );
1063 								} else {
1064 									newDefer[ action ]( returned );
1065 								}
1066 							});
1067 						} else {
1068 							deferred[ handler ]( newDefer[ action ] );
1069 1070 						}
1071 					});
1072 				}).promise();
1073 			},
1074 			// Get a promise for this deferred
1075 			// If obj is provided, the promise aspect is added to the object
1076 			promise: function( obj ) {
1077 				if ( obj == null ) {
1078 					if ( promise ) {
1079 						return promise;
1080 					}
1081 					promise = obj = {};
1082 				}
1083 				var i = promiseMethods.length;
1084 				while( i-- ) {
1085 					obj[ promiseMethods[i] ] = deferred[ promiseMethods[i] ];
1086 				}
1087 				return obj;
1088 			}
1089 		});
1090 		// Make sure only one callback list will be used
1091 		deferred.done( failDeferred.cancel ).fail( deferred.cancel );
1092 		// Unexpose cancel
1093 1094 		delete deferred.cancel;
1095 		// Call given func if any
1096 		if ( func ) {
1097 			func.call( deferred, deferred );
1098 		}
1099 		return deferred;
1100 	},
1101 
1102 	// Deferred helper
1103 	when: function( firstParam ) {
1104 		var args = arguments,
1105 			i = 0,
1106 			length = args.length,
1107 			count = length,
1108 			deferred = length <= 1 && firstParam && jQuery.isFunction( firstParam.promise ) ?
1109 				firstParam :
1110 				jQuery.Deferred();
1111 		function resolveFunc( i ) {
1112 			return function( value ) {
1113 				args[ i ] = arguments.length > 1 ? sliceDeferred.call( arguments, 0 ) : value;
1114 				if ( !( --count ) ) {
1115 					// Strange bug in FF4:
1116 					// Values changed onto the arguments object sometimes end up as undefined values
1117 					// outside the $.when method. Cloning the object into a fresh array solves the issue
1118 					deferred.resolveWith( deferred, sliceDeferred.call( args, 0 ) );
1119 				}
1120 			};
1121 		}
1122 		if ( length > 1 ) {
1123 			for( ; i < length; i++ ) {
1124 				if ( args[ i ] && jQuery.isFunction( args[ i ].promise ) ) {
1125 					args[ i ].promise().then( resolveFunc(i), deferred.reject );
1126 				} else {
1127 					--count;
1128 				}
1129 			}
1130 			if ( !count ) {
1131 				deferred.resolveWith( deferred, args );
1132 			}
1133 		} else if ( deferred !== firstParam ) {
1134 			deferred.resolveWith( deferred, length ? [ firstParam ] : [] );
1135 		}
1136 		return deferred.promise();
1137 	}
1138 });

1357 	// Technique from Juriy Zaytsev
1358 	// http://thinkweb2.com/projects/prototype/detecting-event-support-without-browser-sniffing/
1359 	// We only care about the case where non-standard event systems
1360 	// are used, namely in IE. Short-circuiting here helps us to
1361 	// avoid an eval call (in setAttribute) which can cause CSP
1362 	// to go haywire. See: https://developer.mozilla.org/en/Security/CSP

1371 			if ( !isSupported ) {
1372 				div.setAttribute( eventName, "return;" );
1373 				isSupported = ( typeof div[ eventName ] === "function" );
1374 			}
1375 			support[ i + "Bubbles" ] = isSupported;
1376 		}
1377 	}
1378 
1379 	return support;
1380 })();
1381 
1382 // Keep track of boxModel
1383 jQuery.boxModel = jQuery.support.boxModel;

1388 var rbrace = /^(?:\{.*\}|\[.*\])$/,
1389 	rmultiDash = /([a-z])([A-Z])/g;

1391 jQuery.extend({
1392 	cache: {},
1393 
1394 	// Please use with caution
1395 	uuid: 0,
1396 
1397 	// Unique for each copy of jQuery on the page
1398 	// Non-digits removed to match rinlinejQuery
1399 	expando: "jQuery" + ( jQuery.fn.jquery + Math.random() ).replace( /\D/g, "" ),
1400 
1401 	// The following elements throw uncatchable exceptions if you
1402 	// attempt to add expando properties to them.
1403 	noData: {
1404 		"embed": true,
1405 		// Ban all objects except for Flash (which handle expandos)
1406 		"object": "clsid:D27CDB6E-AE6D-11cf-96B8-444553540000",
1407 		"applet": true
1408 	},
1409 
1410 	hasData: function( elem ) {
1411 		elem = elem.nodeType ? jQuery.cache[ elem[jQuery.expando] ] : elem[ jQuery.expando ];
1412 
1413 		return !!elem && !isEmptyDataObject( elem );
1414 	},
1415 
1416 	data: function( elem, name, data, pvt /* Internal Use Only */ ) {
1417 		if ( !jQuery.acceptData( elem ) ) {
1418 			return;
1419 		}
1420 
1421 		var internalKey = jQuery.expando, getByName = typeof name === "string", thisCache,
1422 
1423 			// We have to handle DOM nodes and JS objects differently because IE6-7
1424 			// can't GC object references properly across the DOM-JS boundary
1425 			isNode = elem.nodeType,
1426 
1427 			// Only DOM nodes need the global jQuery cache; JS object data is
1428 			// attached directly to the object so GC can occur automatically
1429 			cache = isNode ? jQuery.cache : elem,
1430 
1431 			// Only defining an ID for JS objects if its cache already exists allows
1432 			// the code to shortcut on the same path as a DOM node with no cache
1433 			id = isNode ? elem[ jQuery.expando ] : elem[ jQuery.expando ] && jQuery.expando;
1434 
1435 		// Avoid doing any more work than we need to when trying to get data on an
1436 		// object that has no data at all
1437 		if ( (!id || (pvt && id && !cache[ id ][ internalKey ])) && getByName && data === undefined ) {
1438 			return;
1439 		}
1440 
1441 		if ( !id ) {
1442 			// Only DOM nodes need a new unique ID for each element since their data
1443 			// ends up in the global cache
1444 			if ( isNode ) {
1445 				elem[ jQuery.expando ] = id = ++jQuery.uuid;
1446 			} else {
1447 				id = jQuery.expando;
1448 			}
1449 		}
1450 
1451 		if ( !cache[ id ] ) {
1452 			cache[ id ] = {};
1453 
1454 			// TODO: This is a hack for 1.5 ONLY. Avoids exposing jQuery
1455 			// metadata on plain JS objects when the object is serialized using
1456 			// JSON.stringify
1457 			if ( !isNode ) {
1458 				cache[ id ].toJSON = jQuery.noop;
1459 			}
1460 		}
1461 
1462 		// An object can be passed to jQuery.data instead of a key/value pair; this gets
1463 		// shallow copied over onto the existing cache
1464 		if ( typeof name === "object" || typeof name === "function" ) {
1465 			if ( pvt ) {
1466 				cache[ id ][ internalKey ] = jQuery.extend(cache[ id ][ internalKey ], name);
1467 			} else {
1468 				cache[ id ] = jQuery.extend(cache[ id ], name);
1469 			}
1470 		}
1471 
1472 		thisCache = cache[ id ];
1473 
1474 		// Internal jQuery data is stored in a separate object inside the object's data
1475 		// cache in order to avoid key collisions between internal data and user-defined
1476 		// data
1477 		if ( pvt ) {
1478 			if ( !thisCache[ internalKey ] ) {
1479 				thisCache[ internalKey ] = {};
1480 			}
1481 
1482 			thisCache = thisCache[ internalKey ];
1483 		}
1484 
1485 		if ( data !== undefined ) {
1486 			thisCache[ jQuery.camelCase( name ) ] = data;
1487 		}
1488 
1489 		// TODO: This is a hack for 1.5 ONLY. It will be removed in 1.6. Users should
1490 		// not attempt to inspect the internal events object using jQuery.data, as this
1491 		// internal data object is undocumented and subject to change.
1492 		if ( name === "events" && !thisCache[name] ) {
1493 			return thisCache[ internalKey ] && thisCache[ internalKey ].events;
1494 		}
1495 
1496 		return getByName ? thisCache[ jQuery.camelCase( name ) ] : thisCache;
1497 	},
1498 
1499 	removeData: function( elem, name, pvt /* Internal Use Only */ ) {
1500 		if ( !jQuery.acceptData( elem ) ) {
1501 			return;
1502 		}
1503 
1504 		var internalKey = jQuery.expando, isNode = elem.nodeType,
1505 
1506 			// See jQuery.data for more information
1507 			cache = isNode ? jQuery.cache : elem,
1508 
1509 			// See jQuery.data for more information
1510 			id = isNode ? elem[ jQuery.expando ] : jQuery.expando;
1511 1512 
		// If there is already no cache entry for this object, there is no
1513 		// purpose in continuing
1514 		if ( !cache[ id ] ) {
1515 			return;
1516 		}
1517 
1518 		if ( name ) {
1519 			var thisCache = pvt ? cache[ id ][ internalKey ] : cache[ id ];
1520 
1521 			if ( thisCache ) {
1522 				delete thisCache[ name ];
1523 
1524 				// If there is no data left in the cache, we want to continue
1525 				// and let the cache object itself get destroyed
1526 				if ( !isEmptyDataObject(thisCache) ) {
1527 					return;
1528 				}
1529 			}
1530 		}
1531 
1532 		// See jQuery.data for more information
1533 		if ( pvt ) {
1534 			delete cache[ id ][ internalKey ];
1535 
1536 			// Don't destroy the parent cache unless the internal data object
1537 			// had been the only thing left in it
1538 			if ( !isEmptyDataObject(cache[ id ]) ) {
1539 				return;
1540 			}
1541 		}
1542 
1543 		var internalCache = cache[ id ][ internalKey ];
1544 
1545 		// Browsers that fail expando deletion also refuse to delete expandos on
1546 		// the window, but it will allow it on all other JS objects; other browsers
1547 		// don't care
1548 		if ( jQuery.support.deleteExpando || cache != window ) {
1549 			delete cache[ id ];
1550 		} else {
1551 			cache[ id ] = null;
1552 		}
1553 
1554 		// We destroyed the entire user cache at once because it's faster than
1555 		// iterating through each key, but we need to continue to persist internal
1556 		// data if it existed
1557 		if ( internalCache ) {
1558 			cache[ id ] = {};
1559 			// TODO: This is a hack for 1.5 ONLY. Avoids exposing jQuery
1560 			// metadata on plain JS objects when the object is serialized using
1561 			// JSON.stringify
1562 			if ( !isNode ) {
1563 				cache[ id ].toJSON = jQuery.noop;
1564 			}
1565 
1566 			cache[ id ][ internalKey ] = internalCache;
1567 
1568 		// Otherwise, we need to eliminate the expando on the node to avoid
1569 		// false lookups in the cache for entries that no longer exist
1570 		} else if ( isNode ) {
1571 			// IE does not allow us to delete expando properties from nodes,
1572 			// nor does it have a removeAttribute function on Document nodes;
1573 			// we must handle all of these cases
1574 			if ( jQuery.support.deleteExpando ) {
1575 				delete elem[ jQuery.expando ];
1576 			} else if ( elem.removeAttribute ) {
1577 				elem.removeAttribute( jQuery.expando );
1578 			} else {
1579 				elem[ jQuery.expando ] = null;
1580 			}
1581 		}
1582 	},
1583 
1584 	// For internal use only.
1585 	_data: function( elem, name, data ) {
1586 		return jQuery.data( elem, name, data, true );
1587 	},
1588 
1589 	// A method for determining if a DOM node can handle the data expando
1590 	acceptData: function( elem ) {
1591 		if ( elem.nodeName ) {
1592 			var match = jQuery.noData[ elem.nodeName.toLowerCase() ];
1593 
1594 			if ( match ) {
1595 				return !(match === true || elem.getAttribute("classid") !== match);
1596 			}
1597 		}
1598 
1599 		return true;
1600 	}
1601 });

1603 jQuery.fn.extend({
1604 	data: function( key, value ) {
1605 		var data = null;
1606 
1607 		if ( typeof key === "undefined" ) {
1608 			if ( this.length ) {
1609 				data = jQuery.data( this[0] );
1610 
1611 				if ( this[0].nodeType === 1 ) {
1612 			    var attr = this[0].attributes, name;
1613 					for ( var i = 0, l = attr.length; i < l; i++ ) {
1614 						name = attr[i].name;
1615 
1616 						if ( name.indexOf( "data-" ) === 0 ) {
1617 							name = jQuery.camelCase( name.substring(5) );
1618 
1619 							dataAttr( this[0], name, data[ name ] );
1620 						}
1621 					}
1622 				}
1623 			}
1624 
1625 			return data;
1626 
1627 		} else if ( typeof key === "object" ) {
1628 			return this.each(function() {
1629 				jQuery.data( this, key );
1630 			});
1631 		}
1632 
1633 		var parts = key.split(".");
1634 		parts[1] = parts[1] ? "." + parts[1] : "";
1635 
1636 		if ( value === undefined ) {
1637 			data = this.triggerHandler("getData" + parts[1] + "!", [parts[0]]);
1638 
1639 			// Try to fetch any internally stored data first
1640 			if ( data === undefined && this.length ) {
1641 				data = jQuery.data( this[0], key );
1642 				data = dataAttr( this[0], key, data );
1643 			}
1644 
1645 			return data === undefined && parts[1] ?
1646 				this.data( parts[0] ) :
1647 				data;
1648 
1649 		} else {
1650 			return this.each(function() {
1651 				var $this = jQuery( this ),
1652 					args = [ parts[0], value ];
1653 
1654 				$this.triggerHandler( "setData" + parts[1] + "!", args );
1655 				jQuery.data( this, key, value );
1656 				$this.triggerHandler( "changeData" + parts[1] + "!", args );
1657 1658 			});
1659 		}
1660 	},
1661 
1662 	removeData: function( key ) {
1663 		return this.each(function() {
1664 			jQuery.removeData( this, key );
1665 		});
1666 	}
1667 });
1668 
1669 function dataAttr( elem, key, data ) {
1670 	// If nothing was found internally, try to fetch any
1671 	// data from the HTML5 data-* attribute
1672 	if ( data === undefined && elem.nodeType === 1 ) {
1673 		var name = "data-" + key.replace( rmultiDash, "$1-$2" ).toLowerCase();
1674 
1675 		data = elem.getAttribute( name );
1676 
1677 		if ( typeof data === "string" ) {
1678 			try {
1679 				data = data === "true" ? true :
1680 				data === "false" ? false :
1681 				data === "null" ? null :
1682 				!jQuery.isNaN( data ) ? parseFloat( data ) :
1683 					rbrace.test( data ) ? jQuery.parseJSON( data ) :
1684 					data;
1685 			} catch( e ) {}
1686 
1687 			// Make sure we set the data so it isn't changed later
1688 			jQuery.data( elem, key, data );
1689 
1690 		} else {
1691 			data = undefined;
1692 		}
1693 	}
1694 
1695 	return data;
1696 }
1697 
1698 // TODO: This is a hack for 1.5 ONLY to allow objects with a single toJSON
1699 // property to be considered empty objects; this property always exists in
1700 // order to make sure JSON.stringify does not expose internal metadata
1701 function isEmptyDataObject( obj ) {
1702 	for ( var name in obj ) {
1703 		if ( name !== "toJSON" ) {
1704 			return false;
1705 		}
1706 	}
1707 
1708 	return true;
1709 }

1714 function handleQueueMarkDefer( elem, type, src ) {
1715 	var deferDataKey = type + "defer",
1716 		queueDataKey = type + "queue",
1717 		markDataKey = type + "mark",
1718 		defer = jQuery.data( elem, deferDataKey, undefined, true );
1719 	if ( defer &&
1720 		( src === "queue" || !jQuery.data( elem, queueDataKey, undefined, true ) ) &&
1721 		( src === "mark" || !jQuery.data( elem, markDataKey, undefined, true ) ) ) {
1722 		// Give room for hard-coded callbacks to fire first
1723 		// and eventually mark/queue something else on the element
1724 		setTimeout( function() {
1725 			if ( !jQuery.data( elem, queueDataKey, undefined, true ) &&
1726 				!jQuery.data( elem, markDataKey, undefined, true ) ) {
1727 				jQuery.removeData( elem, deferDataKey, true );
1728 				defer.resolve();
1729 			}
1730 		}, 0 );
1731 	}
1732 }
1733 
1734 jQuery.extend({
1735 
1736 	_mark: function( elem, type ) {
1737 		if ( elem ) {
1738 			type = (type || "fx") + "mark";
1739 			jQuery.data( elem, type, (jQuery.data(elem,type,undefined,true) || 0) + 1, true );
1740 		}
1741 	},
1742 
1743 	_unmark: function( force, elem, type ) {
1744 		if ( force !== true ) {
1745 			type = elem;
1746 			elem = force;
1747 			force = false;
1748 		}
1749 		if ( elem ) {
1750 			type = type || "fx";
1751 			var key = type + "mark",
1752 				count = force ? 0 : ( (jQuery.data( elem, key, undefined, true) || 1 ) - 1 );
1753 			if ( count ) {
1754 				jQuery.data( elem, key, count, true );
1755 			} else {
1756 				jQuery.removeData( elem, key, true );
1757 				handleQueueMarkDefer( elem, type, "mark" );
1758 			}
1759 		}
1760 	},
1761 
1762 	queue: function( elem, type, data ) {
1763 		if ( elem ) {
1764 			type = (type || "fx") + "queue";
1765 			var q = jQuery.data( elem, type, undefined, true );
1766 			// Speed up dequeue by getting out quickly if this is just a lookup
1767 			if ( data ) {
1768 				if ( !q || jQuery.isArray(data) ) {
1769 					q = jQuery.data( elem, type, jQuery.makeArray(data), true );
1770 				} else {
1771 					q.push( data );
1772 				}
1773 			}
1774 			return q || [];
1775 		}
1776 	},
1777 
1778 	dequeue: function( elem, type ) {
1779 		type = type || "fx";
1780 
1781 		var queue = jQuery.queue( elem, type ),
1782 			fn = queue.shift(),
1783 			defer;
1784 
1785 		// If the fx queue is dequeued, always remove the progress sentinel
1786 		if ( fn === "inprogress" ) {
1787 			fn = queue.shift();
1788 		}
1789 
1790 		if ( fn ) {
1791 			// Add a progress sentinel to prevent the fx queue from being
1792 			// automatically dequeued
1793 			if ( type === "fx" ) {
1794 				queue.unshift("inprogress");
1795 			}
1796 
1797 			fn.call(elem, function() {
1798 				jQuery.dequeue(elem, type);
1799 			});
1800 		}
1801 
1802 		if ( !queue.length ) {
1803 			jQuery.removeData( elem, type + "queue", true );
1804 			handleQueueMarkDefer( elem, type, "queue" );
1805 		}
1806 	}
1807 });

1809 jQuery.fn.extend({
1810 	queue: function( type, data ) {
1811 		if ( typeof type !== "string" ) {
1812 			data = type;
1813 			type = "fx";
1814 		}
1815 
1816 		if ( data === undefined ) {
1817 			return jQuery.queue( this[0], type );
1818 		}
1819 		return this.each(function() {
1820 			var queue = jQuery.queue( this, type, data );
1821 
1822 			if ( type === "fx" && queue[0] !== "inprogress" ) {
1823 				jQuery.dequeue( this, type );
1824 			}
1825 		});
1826 	},
1827 	dequeue: function( type ) {
1828 		return this.each(function() {
1829 			jQuery.dequeue( this, type );
1830 		});
1831 	},
1832 	// Based off of the plugin by Clint Helfers, with permission.
1833 	// http://blindsignals.com/index.php/2009/07/jquery-delay/
1834 	delay: function( time, type ) {
1835 		time = jQuery.fx ? jQuery.fx.speeds[time] || time : time;
1836 		type = type || "fx";
1837 
1838 		return this.queue( type, function() {
1839 			var elem = this;
1840 			setTimeout(function() {
1841 				jQuery.dequeue( elem, type );
1842 			}, time );
1843 		});
1844 	},
1845 	clearQueue: function( type ) {
1846 		return this.queue( type || "fx", [] );
1847 	},
1848 	// Get a promise resolved when queues of a certain type
1849 	// are emptied (fx is the type by default)
1850 	promise: function( type, object ) {
1851 		if ( typeof type !== "string" ) {
1852 			object = type;
1853 			type = undefined;
1854 		}
1855 		type = type || "fx";
1856 		var defer = jQuery.Deferred(),
1857 			elements = this,
1858 			i = elements.length,
1859 			count = 1,
1860 			deferDataKey = type + "defer",
1861 			queueDataKey = type + "queue",
1862 			markDataKey = type + "mark",
1863 			tmp;
1864 		function resolve() {
1865 			if ( !( --count ) ) {
1866 				defer.resolveWith( elements, [ elements ] );
1867 			}
1868 		}
1869 		while( i-- ) {
1870 			if (( tmp = jQuery.data( elements[ i ], deferDataKey, undefined, true ) ||
1871 					( jQuery.data( elements[ i ], queueDataKey, undefined, true ) ||
1872 						jQuery.data( elements[ i ], markDataKey, undefined, true ) ) &&
1873 					jQuery.data( elements[ i ], deferDataKey, jQuery._Deferred(), true ) )) {
1874 				count++;
1875 				tmp.done( resolve );
1876 			}
1877 		}
1878 		resolve();
1879 		return defer.promise();
1880 	}
1881 });

1886 var rclass = /[\n\t\r]/g,
1887 	rspace = /\s+/,
1888 	rreturn = /\r/g,
1889 	rtype = /^(?:button|input)$/i,
1890 	rfocusable = /^(?:button|input|object|select|textarea)$/i,
1891 	rclickable = /^a(?:rea)?$/i,
1892 	rboolean = /^(?:autofocus|autoplay|async|checked|controls|defer|disabled|hidden|loop|multiple|open|readonly|required|scoped|selected)$/i,
1893 	rinvalidChar = /\:/,

1896 jQuery.fn.extend({
1897 	attr: function( name, value ) {
1898 		return jQuery.access( this, name, value, true, jQuery.attr );
1899 	},
1900 
1901 	removeAttr: function( name ) {
1902 		return this.each(function() {
1903 			jQuery.removeAttr( this, name );
1904 		});
1905 	},
1906 	
1907 	prop: function( name, value ) {
1908 		return jQuery.access( this, name, value, true, jQuery.prop );
1909 	},
1910 	
1911 	removeProp: function( name ) {
1912 		name = jQuery.propFix[ name ] || name;
1913 		return this.each(function() {
1914 			// try/catch handles cases where IE balks (such as removing a property on window)
1915 			try {
1916 				this[ name ] = undefined;
1917 				delete this[ name ];
1918 			} catch( e ) {}
1919 		});
1920 	},
1921 
1922 	addClass: function( value ) {
1923 		if ( jQuery.isFunction( value ) ) {
1924 			return this.each(function(i) {
1925 				var self = jQuery(this);
1926 				self.addClass( value.call(this, i, self.attr("class") || "") );
1927 			});
1928 		}
1929 
1930 		if ( value && typeof value === "string" ) {
1931 			var classNames = (value || "").split( rspace );
1932 
1933 			for ( var i = 0, l = this.length; i < l; i++ ) {
1934 				var elem = this[i];
1935 
1936 				if ( elem.nodeType === 1 ) {
1937 					if ( !elem.className ) {
1938 						elem.className = value;
1939 
1940 					} else {
1941 						var className = " " + elem.className + " ",
1942 							setClass = elem.className;
1943 
1944 						for ( var c = 0, cl = classNames.length; c < cl; c++ ) {
1945 							if ( className.indexOf( " " + classNames[c] + " " ) < 0 ) {
1946 								setClass += " " + classNames[c];
1947 							}
1948 						}
1949 						elem.className = jQuery.trim( setClass );
1950 					}
1951 				}
1952 			}
1953 		}
1954 
1955 		return this;
1956 	},
1957 
1958 	removeClass: function( value ) {
1959 		if ( jQuery.isFunction(value) ) {
1960 			return this.each(function(i) {
1961 				var self = jQuery(this);
1962 				self.removeClass( value.call(this, i, self.attr("class")) );
1963 			});
1964 		}
1965 
1966 		if ( (value && typeof value === "string") || value === undefined ) {
1967 			var classNames = (value || "").split( rspace );
1968 
1969 			for ( var i = 0, l = this.length; i < l; i++ ) {
1970 				var elem = this[i];
1971 
1972 				if ( elem.nodeType === 1 && elem.className ) {
1973 					if ( value ) {
1974 						var className = (" " + elem.className + " ").replace(rclass, " ");
1975 						for ( var c = 0, cl = classNames.length; c < cl; c++ ) {
1976 							className = className.replace(" " + classNames[c] + " ", " ");
1977 						}
1978 						elem.className = jQuery.trim( className );
1979 
1980 					} else {
1981 						elem.className = "";
1982 					}
1983 				}
1984 			}
1985 		}
1986 
1987 		return this;
1988 	},
1989 
1990 	toggleClass: function( value, stateVal ) {
1991 		var type = typeof value,
1992 			isBool = typeof stateVal === "boolean";
1993 
1994 		if ( jQuery.isFunction( value ) ) {
1995 			return this.each(function(i) {
1996 				var self = jQuery(this);
1997 				self.toggleClass( value.call(this, i, self.attr("class"), stateVal), stateVal );
1998 			});
1999 		}
2000 
2001 		return this.each(function() {
2002 			if ( type === "string" ) {
2003 				// toggle individual class names
2004 				var className,
2005 					i = 0,
2006 					self = jQuery( this ),
2007 					state = stateVal,
2008 					classNames = value.split( rspace );
2009 
2010 				while ( (className = classNames[ i++ ]) ) {
2011 					// check each className given, space seperated list

2020 				}
2021 
2022 				// toggle whole className
2023 				this.className = this.className || value === false ? "" : jQuery._data( this, "__className__" ) || "";

2025 		});

2515 /*
2516  * A number of helper functions used for managing events.
2517  * Many of the ideas behind this code originated from
2518  * Dean Edwards' addEvent library.
2519  */
2520 jQuery.event = {
2521 
2522 	// Bind an event to an element
2523 	// Original by Dean Edwards
2524 	add: function( elem, types, handler, data ) {
2525 		if ( elem.nodeType === 3 || elem.nodeType === 8 ) {
2526 			return;
2527 		}
2528 
2529 		if ( handler === false ) {
2530 			handler = returnFalse;
2531 		} else if ( !handler ) {
2532 			// Fixes bug #7229. Fix recommended by jdalton
2533 			return;
2534 		}
2535 
2536 		var handleObjIn, handleObj;
2537 
2538 		if ( handler.handler ) {
2539 			handleObjIn = handler;
2540 			handler = handleObjIn.handler;
2541 		}
2542 
2543 		// Make sure that the function being executed has a unique ID
2544 		if ( !handler.guid ) {
2545 			handler.guid = jQuery.guid++;
2546 		}
2547 
2548 		// Init the element's event structure
2549 		var elemData = jQuery._data( elem );
2550 
2551 		// If no elemData is found then we must be trying to bind to one of the
2552 		// banned noData elements
2553 		if ( !elemData ) {
2554 			return;
2555 		}
2556 
2557 		var events = elemData.events,
2558 			eventHandle = elemData.handle;
2559 
2560 		if ( !events ) {
2561 			elemData.events = events = {};
2562 		}
2563 
2564 		if ( !eventHandle ) {
2565 			elemData.handle = eventHandle = function( e ) {
2566 				// Discard the second event of a jQuery.event.trigger() and
2567 				// when an event is called after a page has unloaded
2568 				return typeof jQuery !== "undefined" && (!e || jQuery.event.triggered !== e.type) ?
2569 					jQuery.event.handle.apply( eventHandle.elem, arguments ) :
2570 					undefined;
2571 			};
2572 		}
2573 
2574 		// Add elem as a property of the handle function
2575 		// This is to prevent a memory leak with non-native events in IE.
2576 		eventHandle.elem = elem;
2577 
2578 		// Handle multiple events separated by a space
2579 		// jQuery(...).bind("mouseover mouseout", fn);
2580 		types = types.split(" ");
2581 
2582 		var type, i = 0, namespaces;
2583 
2584 		while ( (type = types[ i++ ]) ) {
2585 			handleObj = handleObjIn ?
2586 				jQuery.extend({}, handleObjIn) :
2587 				{ handler: handler, data: data };
2588 
2589 			// Namespaced event handlers
2590 			if ( type.indexOf(".") > -1 ) {
2591 				namespaces = type.split(".");
2592 				type = namespaces.shift();
2593 				handleObj.namespace = namespaces.slice(0).sort().join(".");
2594 
2595 			} else {
2596 				namespaces = [];
2597 				handleObj.namespace = "";
2598 			}
2599 
2600 			handleObj.type = type;
2601 			if ( !handleObj.guid ) {
2602 				handleObj.guid = handler.guid;
2603 			}
2604 
2605 			// Get the current list of functions bound to this event
2606 			var handlers = events[ type ],
2607 				special = jQuery.event.special[ type ] || {};
2608 
2609 			// Init the event handler queue
2610 			if ( !handlers ) {
2611 				handlers = events[ type ] = [];
2612 
2613 				// Check for a special event handler
2614 				// Only use addEventListener/attachEvent if the special
2615 				// events handler returns false
2616 				if ( !special.setup || special.setup.call( elem, data, namespaces, eventHandle ) === false ) {
2617 					// Bind the global event handler to the element
2618 					if ( elem.addEventListener ) {
2619 						elem.addEventListener( type, eventHandle, false );
2620 
2621 					} else if ( elem.attachEvent ) {
2622 						elem.attachEvent( "on" + type, eventHandle );
2623 					}
2624 				}
2625 			}
2626 
2627 			if ( special.add ) {
2628 				special.add.call( elem, handleObj );
2629 
2630 				if ( !handleObj.handler.guid ) {
2631 					handleObj.handler.guid = handler.guid;
2632 				}
2633 			}
2634 
2635 			// Add the function to the element's handler list
2636 			handlers.push( handleObj );
2637 
2638 			// Keep track of which events have been used, for event optimization
2639 			jQuery.event.global[ type ] = true;
2640 		}
2641 
2642 		// Nullify elem to prevent memory leaks in IE
2643 		elem = null;
2644 	},
2645 
2646 	global: {},
2647 
2648 	// Detach an event or set of events from an element
2649 	remove: function( elem, types, handler, pos ) {
2650 		// don't do events on text and comment nodes
2651 		if ( elem.nodeType === 3 || elem.nodeType === 8 ) {
2652 			return;
2653 		}
2654 
2655 		if ( handler === false ) {
2656 			handler = returnFalse;

3069 jQuery.Event = function( src, props ) {
3070 	// Allow instantiation without the 'new' keyword
3071 	if ( !this.preventDefault ) {
3072 		return new jQuery.Event( src, props );
3073 	}
3074 
3075 	// Event object
3076 	if ( src && src.type ) {
3077 		this.originalEvent = src;
3078 		this.type = src.type;
3079 
3080 		// Events bubbling up the document may have been marked as prevented
3081 		// by a handler lower down the tree; reflect the correct value.
3082 		this.isDefaultPrevented = (src.defaultPrevented || src.returnValue === false ||
3083 			src.getPreventDefault && src.getPreventDefault()) ? returnTrue : returnFalse;
3084 
3085 	// Event type
3086 	} else {
3087 		this.type = src;
3088 	}
3089 
3090 	// Put explicitly provided properties onto the event object
3091 	if ( props ) {
3092 		jQuery.extend( this, props );
3093 	}
3094 
3095 	// timeStamp is buggy for some events on Firefox(#3843)
3096 	// So we won't rely on the native value
3097 	this.timeStamp = jQuery.now();
3098 
3099 	// Mark it as fixed
3100 	this[ jQuery.expando ] = true;
3101 };

3110 // jQuery.Event is based on DOM3 Events as specified by the ECMAScript Language Binding
3111 // http://www.w3.org/TR/2003/WD-DOM-Level-3-Events-20030331/ecma-script-binding.html

3113 	preventDefault: function() {
3114 		this.isDefaultPrevented = returnTrue;
3115 
3116 		var e = this.originalEvent;
3117 		if ( !e ) {
3118 			return;
3119 		}

3121 		// if preventDefault exists run it on the original event
3122 		if ( e.preventDefault ) {
3123 			e.preventDefault();
3124 
3125 		// otherwise set the returnValue property of the original event to false (IE)
3126 		} else {
3127 			e.returnValue = false;
3128 		}
3129 	},
3130 	stopPropagation: function() {
3131 		this.isPropagationStopped = returnTrue;

3139 			e.stopPropagation();

3142 		e.cancelBubble = true;

3153 // Checks if an event happened on an element within another element
3154 // Used in jQuery.event.special.mouseenter and mouseleave handlers
3155 var withinElement = function( event ) {
3156 	// Check if mouse(over|out) are still within the same parent element
3157 	var parent = event.relatedTarget;
3158 
3159 	// set the correct event type
3160 3161 	event.type = event.data;
3162 
3163 	// Firefox sometimes assigns relatedTarget a XUL element
3164 	// which we cannot access the parentNode property of
3165 	try {
3166 
3167 		// Chrome does something similar, the parentNode property
3168 		// can be accessed but is null.
3169 		if ( parent && parent !== document && !parent.parentNode ) {
3170 			return;
3171 		}
3172 
3173 		// Traverse up the tree
3174 		while ( parent && parent !== this ) {
3175 			parent = parent.parentNode;
3176 		}
3177 
3178 		if ( parent !== this ) {
3179 			// handle event if we actually just moused on to a non sub-element
3180 			jQuery.event.handle.apply( this, arguments );
3181 		}
3182 
3183 	// assuming we've left the element since we most likely mousedover a xul element
3184 	} catch(e) { }
3185 },

3286 			return;
3287 		}
3288 
3289 		if ( data != null || val ) {
3290 			e.type = "change";
3291 			e.liveFired = undefined;
3292 			jQuery.event.trigger( e, arguments[1], elem );
3293 		}
3294 	};
3295 
3296 	jQuery.event.special.change = {
3297 		filters: {
3298 			focusout: testChange,
3299 
3300 			beforedeactivate: testChange,
3301 
3302 			click: function( e ) {
3303 				var elem = e.target, type = jQuery.nodeName( elem, "input" ) ? elem.type : "";
3304 
3305 				if ( type === "radio" || type === "checkbox" || jQuery.nodeName( elem, "select" ) ) {
3306 					testChange.call( this, e );
3307 				}
3308 			},
3309 
3310 			// Change has to be called before submit
3311 			// Keydown will be called before keypress, which is used in submit-event delegation

3313 				var elem = e.target, type = jQuery.nodeName( elem, "input" ) ? elem.type : "";
3314 
3315 				if ( (e.keyCode === 13 && !jQuery.nodeName( elem, "textarea" ) ) ||
3316 					(e.keyCode === 32 && (type === "checkbox" || type === "radio")) ||
3317 					type === "select-multiple" ) {
3318 					testChange.call( this, e );
3319 				}
3320 			},
3321 
3322 			// Beforeactivate happens also before the previous element is blurred
3323 			// with this event you can't trigger a change event, but you can store
3324 			// information
3325 			beforeactivate: function( e ) {
3326 				var elem = e.target;
3327 				jQuery._data( elem, "_change_data", getVal(elem) );
3328 			}
3329 		},
3330

3332 			if ( this.type === "file" ) {
3333 				return false;
3334 			}

3336 			for ( var type in changeFilters ) {

3338 			}

3341 		},

3347 		}

3356 function trigger( type, elem, args ) {
3357 	// Piggyback on a donor event to simulate a different one.
3358 	// Fake originalEvent to avoid donor's stopPropagation, but if the
3359 	// simulated event prevents default then we do the same on the donor.
3360 	// Don't pass args or remember liveFired; they apply to the donor event.
3361 	var event = jQuery.extend( {}, args[ 0 ] );
3362 	event.type = type;
3363 	event.originalEvent = {};
3364 	event.liveFired = undefined;
3365 	jQuery.event.handle.call( elem, event );
3366 	if ( event.isDefaultPrevented() ) {
3367 		args[ 0 ].preventDefault();
3368 	}
3369 }

3371 // Create "bubbling" focus and blur events
3372 if ( !jQuery.support.focusinBubbles ) {
3373 	jQuery.each({ focus: "focusin", blur: "focusout" }, function( orig, fix ) {
3374 
3375 		// Attach a single capturing handler while someone wants focusin/focusout
3376 		var attaches = 0;
3377 
3378 		jQuery.event.special[ fix ] = {
3379 			setup: function() {
3380 				if ( attaches++ === 0 ) {
3381 					document.addEventListener( orig, handler, true );
3382 				}
3383 			},
3384 			teardown: function() {
3385 				if ( --attaches === 0 ) {
3386 					document.removeEventListener( orig, handler, true );
3387 				}
3388 			}
3389 		};
3390 
3391 		function handler( donor ) {
3392 			// Donor event is always a native one; fix it and switch its type.
3393 			// Let focusin/out handler cancel the donor focus/blur event.
3394 			var e = jQuery.event.fix( donor );
3395 			e.type = fix;
3396 			e.originalEvent = {};
3397 			jQuery.event.trigger( e, null, e.target );
3398 			if ( e.isDefaultPrevented() ) {
3399 				donor.preventDefault();
3400 			}
3401 		}
3402 	});

3525 jQuery.each(["live", "die"], function( i, name ) {
3526 	jQuery.fn[ name ] = function( types, data, fn, origSelector /* Internal Use Only */ ) {
3527 		var type, i = 0, match, namespaces, preType,
3528 			selector = origSelector || this.selector,
3529 			context = origSelector ? this : jQuery( this.context );
3530 
3531 		if ( typeof types === "object" && !types.preventDefault ) {
3532 			for ( var key in types ) {
3533 				context[ name ]( key, data, types[key], selector );
3534 			}
3535 
3536 			return this;
3537 		}
3538 
3539 		if ( name === "die" && !types &&
3540 					origSelector && origSelector.charAt(0) === "." ) {
3541 
3542 			context.unbind( origSelector );
3543 
3544 			return this;
3545 		}
3546 
3547 		if ( data === false || jQuery.isFunction( data ) ) {
3548 			fn = data || returnFalse;
3549 			data = undefined;
3550 		}
3551 
3552 		types = (types || "").split(" ");
3553 
3554 		while ( (type = types[ i++ ]) != null ) {
3555 			match = rnamespaces.exec( type );
3556 			namespaces = "";
3557 
3558 			if ( match )  {
3559 				namespaces = match[0];
3560 				type = type.replace( rnamespaces, "" );
3561 			}
3562 
3563 			if ( type === "hover" ) {
3564 				types.push( "mouseenter" + namespaces, "mouseleave" + namespaces );
3565 				continue;
3566 			}
3567 
3568 			preType = type;
3569 
3570 			if ( liveMap[ type ] ) {
3571 				types.push( liveMap[ type ] + namespaces );
3572 				type = type + namespaces;
3573 
3574 			} else {
3575 				type = (liveMap[ type ] || type) + namespaces;
3576 			}
3577 
3578 			if ( name === "live" ) {
3579 				// bind live handler
3580 				for ( var j = 0, l = context.length; j < l; j++ ) {
3581 					jQuery.event.add( context[j], "live." + liveConvert( type, selector ),
3582 						{ data: data, selector: selector, handler: fn, origType: type, origHandler: fn, preType: preType } );
3583 				}
3584 
3585 			} else {
3586 				// unbind live handler
3587 				context.unbind( "live." + liveConvert( type, selector ), fn );
3588 			}
3589 		}
3590 
3591 		return this;
3592 	};
3593 });

3595 function liveHandler( event ) {
3596 	var stop, maxLevel, related, match, handleObj, elem, j, i, l, data, close, namespace, ret,
3597 		elems = [],
3598 		selectors = [],
3599 		events = jQuery._data( this, "events" );
3600 
3601 	// Make sure we avoid non-left-click bubbling in Firefox (#3861) and disabled elements in IE (#6911)
3602 	if ( event.liveFired === this || !events || !events.live || event.target.disabled || event.button && event.type === "click" ) {
3603 		return;
3604 	}
3605 
3606 	if ( event.namespace ) {
3607 		namespace = new RegExp("(^|\\.)" + event.namespace.split(".").join("\\.(?:.*\\.)?") + "(\\.|$)");
3608 	}
3609 
3610 	event.liveFired = this;
3611 
3612 	var live = events.live.slice(0);
3613 
3614 	for ( j = 0; j < live.length; j++ ) {
3615 		handleObj = live[j];
3616 
3617 		if ( handleObj.origType.replace( rnamespaces, "" ) === event.type ) {
3618 			selectors.push( handleObj.selector );
3619 
3620 		} else {
3621 			live.splice( j--, 1 );
3622 		}
3623 	}
3624 
3625 	match = jQuery( event.target ).closest( selectors, event.currentTarget );
3626 
3627 	for ( i = 0, l = match.length; i < l; i++ ) {
3628 		close = match[i];
3629 
3630 		for ( j = 0; j < live.length; j++ ) {
3631 			handleObj = live[j];
3632 
3633 			if ( close.selector === handleObj.selector && (!namespace || namespace.test( handleObj.namespace )) && !close.elem.disabled ) {
3634 				elem = close.elem;
3635 				related = null;
3636 
3637 				// Those two events require additional checking
3638 				if ( handleObj.preType === "mouseenter" || handleObj.preType === "mouseleave" ) {
3639 					event.type = handleObj.preType;
3640 					related = jQuery( event.relatedTarget ).closest( handleObj.selector )[0];
3641 
3642 					// Make sure not to accidentally match a child element with the same selector
3643 					if ( related && jQuery.contains( elem, related ) ) {
3644 						related = elem;
3645 					}
3646 				}
3647 
3648 				if ( !related || related !== elem ) {
3649 					elems.push({ elem: elem, handleObj: handleObj, level: close.level });
3650 				}
3651 			}
3652 		}
3653 	}
3654 
3655 	for ( i = 0, l = elems.length; i < l; i++ ) {
3656 		match = elems[i];
3657 
3658 		if ( maxLevel && match.level > maxLevel ) {
3659 			break;
3660 		}
3661 
3662 		event.currentTarget = match.elem;
3663 		event.data = match.handleObj.data;
3664 		event.handleObj = match.handleObj;
3665 
3666 		ret = match.handleObj.origHandler.apply( match.elem, arguments );
3667 
3668 		if ( ret === false || event.isPropagationStopped() ) {
3669 			maxLevel = match.level;
3670 
3671 			if ( ret === false ) {
3672 				stop = false;
3673 			}
3674 			if ( event.isImmediatePropagationStopped() ) {
3675 				break;
3676 			}
3677 		}
3678 	}
3679 
3680 	return stop;
3681 }
3682 
3683 function liveConvert( type, selector ) {
3684 	return (type && type !== "*" ? type + "." : "") + selector.replace(rperiod, "`").replace(rspaces, "&");
3685 }

3688 	"mousedown mouseup mousemove mouseover mouseout mouseenter mouseleave " +
3689 	"change select submit keydown keypress keyup error").split(" "), function( i, name ) {
3690 
3691 	// Handle event binding
3692 	jQuery.fn[ name ] = function( data, fn ) {
3693 		if ( fn == null ) {
3694 			fn = data;
3695 			data = null;
3696 		}
3697 
3698 		return arguments.length > 0 ?
3699 			this.bind( name, data, fn ) :
3700 			this.trigger( name );
3701 	};
3702 
3703 	if ( jQuery.attrFn ) {
3704 		jQuery.attrFn[ name ] = true;

3709 
3710 /*!
3711  * Sizzle CSS Selector Engine
3712  *  Copyright 2011, The Dojo Foundation
3713  *  Released under the MIT, BSD, and GPL Licenses.
3714  *  More information: http://sizzlejs.com/
3715  */
3716 (function(){
3717 
3718 var chunker = /((?:\((?:\([^()]+\)|[^()]+)+\)|\[(?:\[[^\[\]]*\]|['"][^'"]*['"]|[^\[\]'"]+)+\]|\\.|[^ >+~,(\[\\]+)+|[>+~])(\s*,\s*)?((?:.|\r|\n)*)/g,
3719 	done = 0,
3720 	toString = Object.prototype.toString,
3721 	hasDuplicate = false,
3722 	baseHasDuplicate = true,
3723 	rBackslash = /\\/g,
3724 	rNonWord = /\W/;
3725 
3726 // Here we check if the JavaScript engine is using some sort of
3727 // optimization where it does not always call our comparision
3728 // function. If that is the case, discard the hasDuplicate value.
3729 //   Thus far that includes Google Chrome.
3730 [0, 0].sort(function() {
3731 	baseHasDuplicate = false;
3732 	return 0;
3733 });
3734 
3735 var Sizzle = function( selector, context, results, seed ) {
3736 	results = results || [];
3737 	context = context || document;
3738 
3739 	var origContext = context;
3740 
3741 	if ( context.nodeType !== 1 && context.nodeType !== 9 ) {
3742 		return [];
3743 	}
3744 	
3745 	if ( !selector || typeof selector !== "string" ) {
3746 		return results;
3747 	}
3748 
3749 	var m, set, checkSet, extra, ret, cur, pop, i,
3750 		prune = true,
3751 		contextXML = Sizzle.isXML( context ),
3752 		parts = [],
3753 		soFar = selector;
3754 	
3755 	// Reset the position of the chunker regexp (start from head)
3756 	do {
3757 		chunker.exec( "" );
3758 		m = chunker.exec( soFar );
3759 
3760 		if ( m ) {
3761 			soFar = m[3];
3762 		
3763 			parts.push( m[1] );
3764 		
3765 			if ( m[2] ) {
3766 				extra = m[3];
3767 				break;
3768 			}
3769 		}
3770 	} while ( m );
3771 
3772 	if ( parts.length > 1 && origPOS.exec( selector ) ) {
3773 
3774 		if ( parts.length === 2 && Expr.relative[ parts[0] ] ) {
3775 			set = posProcess( parts[0] + parts[1], context );
3776 
3777 		} else {
3778 			set = Expr.relative[ parts[0] ] ?
3779 				[ context ] :
3780 				Sizzle( parts.shift(), context );
3781 
3782 			while ( parts.length ) {
3783 				selector = parts.shift();
3784 
3785 				if ( Expr.relative[ selector ] ) {
3786 					selector += parts.shift();
3787 				}
3788 				
3789 				set = posProcess( selector, set );
3790 			}
3791 		}
3792 
3793 	} else {
3794 		// Take a shortcut and set the context if the root selector is an ID
3795 		// (but not if it'll be faster if the inner selector is an ID)
3796 		if ( !seed && parts.length > 1 && context.nodeType === 9 && !contextXML &&
3797 				Expr.match.ID.test(parts[0]) && !Expr.match.ID.test(parts[parts.length - 1]) ) {
3798 
3799 			ret = Sizzle.find( parts.shift(), context, contextXML );
3800 			context = ret.expr ?
3801 				Sizzle.filter( ret.expr, ret.set )[0] :
3802 				ret.set[0];
3803 		}
3804 
3805 		if ( context ) {
3806 			ret = seed ?
3807 				{ expr: parts.pop(), set: makeArray(seed) } :
3808 				Sizzle.find( parts.pop(), parts.length === 1 && (parts[0] === "~" || parts[0] === "+") && context.parentNode ? context.parentNode : context, contextXML );
3809 
3810 			set = ret.expr ?
3811 				Sizzle.filter( ret.expr, ret.set ) :
3812 				ret.set;
3813 
3814 			if ( parts.length > 0 ) {
3815 				checkSet = makeArray( set );
3816 
3817 			} else {
3818 				prune = false;
3819 			}
3820 
3821 			while ( parts.length ) {
3822 				cur = parts.pop();
3823 				pop = cur;
3824 
3825 				if ( !Expr.relative[ cur ] ) {
3826 					cur = "";
3827 				} else {
3828 					pop = parts.pop();
3829 				}
3830 
3831 				if ( pop == null ) {
3832 					pop = context;
3833 				}
3834 
3835 				Expr.relative[ cur ]( checkSet, pop, contextXML );
3836 			}
3837 
3838 		} else {
3839 			checkSet = parts = [];
3840 		}
3841 	}
3842 
3843 	if ( !checkSet ) {
3844 		checkSet = set;
3845 	}
3846 
3847 	if ( !checkSet ) {
3848 		Sizzle.error( cur || selector );
3849 	}
3850 
3851 	if ( toString.call(checkSet) === "[object Array]" ) {
3852 		if ( !prune ) {
3853 			results.push.apply( results, checkSet );
3854 
3855 		} else if ( context && context.nodeType === 1 ) {
3856 			for ( i = 0; checkSet[i] != null; i++ ) {
3857 				if ( checkSet[i] && (checkSet[i] === true || checkSet[i].nodeType === 1 && Sizzle.contains(context, checkSet[i])) ) {
3858 					results.push( set[i] );
3859 				}
3860 			}
3861 
3862 		} else {
3863 			for ( i = 0; checkSet[i] != null; i++ ) {
3864 				if ( checkSet[i] && checkSet[i].nodeType === 1 ) {
3865 					results.push( set[i] );
3866 				}
3867 			}
3868 		}
3869 
3870 	} else {
3871 		makeArray( checkSet, results );
3872 	}
3873 
3874 	if ( extra ) {
3875 		Sizzle( extra, origContext, results, seed );
3876 		Sizzle.uniqueSort( results );
3877 	}
3878 
3879 	return results;
3880 };
3881 
3882 Sizzle.uniqueSort = function( results ) {
3883 	if ( sortOrder ) {
3884 		hasDuplicate = baseHasDuplicate;
3885 		results.sort( sortOrder );
3886 
3887 		if ( hasDuplicate ) {
3888 			for ( var i = 1; i < results.length; i++ ) {
3889 				if ( results[i] === results[ i - 1 ] ) {
3890 					results.splice( i--, 1 );
3891 				}
3892 			}
3893 		}
3894 	}
3895 
3896 	return results;
3897 };
3898 
3899 Sizzle.matches = function( expr, set ) {
3900 	return Sizzle( expr, null, null, set );
3901 };
3902 
3903 Sizzle.matchesSelector = function( node, expr ) {
3904 	return Sizzle( expr, null, null, [node] ).length > 0;
3905 };
3906 
3907 Sizzle.find = function( expr, context, isXML ) {
3908 	var set;
3909 
3910 	if ( !expr ) {
3911 		return [];
3912 	}
3913 
3914 	for ( var i = 0, l = Expr.order.length; i < l; i++ ) {
3915 		var match,
3916 			type = Expr.order[i];
3917 		
3918 		if ( (match = Expr.leftMatch[ type ].exec( expr )) ) {
3919 			var left = match[1];
3920 			match.splice( 1, 1 );
3921 
3922 			if ( left.substr( left.length - 1 ) !== "\\" ) {
3923 				match[1] = (match[1] || "").replace( rBackslash, "" );
3924 				set = Expr.find[ type ]( match, context, isXML );
3925 
3926 				if ( set != null ) {
3927 					expr = expr.replace( Expr.match[ type ], "" );
3928 					break;
3929 				}
3930 			}
3931 		}
3932 	}
3933 
3934 	if ( !set ) {
3935 		set = typeof context.getElementsByTagName !== "undefined" ?
3936 			context.getElementsByTagName( "*" ) :
3937 			[];
3938 	}
3939 
3940 	return { set: set, expr: expr };
3941 };

3943 Sizzle.filter = function( expr, set, inplace, not ) {
3944 	var match, anyFound,
3945 		old = expr,
3946 		result = [],
3947 		curLoop = set,
3948 		isXMLFilter = set && set[0] && Sizzle.isXML( set[0] );
3949 
3950 	while ( expr && set.length ) {
3951 		for ( var type in Expr.filter ) {
3952 			if ( (match = Expr.leftMatch[ type ].exec( expr )) != null && match[2] ) {
3953 				var found, item,
3954 					filter = Expr.filter[ type ],
3955 					left = match[1];
3956 
3957 				anyFound = false;
3958 
3959 				match.splice(1,1);
3960 
3961 				if ( left.substr( left.length - 1 ) === "\\" ) {
3962 					continue;
3963 				}
3964 
3965 				if ( curLoop === result ) {
3966 					result = [];
3967 				}
3968 
3969 				if ( Expr.preFilter[ type ] ) {
3970 					match = Expr.preFilter[ type ]( match, curLoop, inplace, result, not, isXMLFilter );
3971 
3972 					if ( !match ) {
3973 						anyFound = found = true;
3974 
3975 					} else if ( match === true ) {
3976 						continue;
3977 					}
3978 				}
3979 
3980 				if ( match ) {
3981 					for ( var i = 0; (item = curLoop[i]) != null; i++ ) {
3982 						if ( item ) {
3983 							found = filter( item, match, i, curLoop );
3984 							var pass = not ^ !!found;
3985 
3986 							if ( inplace && found != null ) {
3987 								if ( pass ) {
3988 									anyFound = true;
3989 
3990 								} else {
3991 									curLoop[i] = false;
3992 								}
3993 
3994 							} else if ( pass ) {
3995 								result.push( item );
3996 								anyFound = true;
3997 							}
3998 						}
3999 					}
4000 				}
4001 
4002 				if ( found !== undefined ) {
4003 					if ( !inplace ) {
4004 						curLoop = result;
4005 					}
4006 
4007 					expr = expr.replace( Expr.match[ type ], "" );
4008 
4009 					if ( !anyFound ) {
4010 						return [];
4011 					}
4012 
4013 					break;
4014 				}
4015 			}
4016 		}
4017 
4018 		// Improper expression
4019 		if ( expr === old ) {
4020 			if ( anyFound == null ) {
4021 				Sizzle.error( expr );
4022 
4023 			} else {
4024 				break;
4025 			}
4026 		}
4027 
4028 		old = expr;
4029 	}
4030 
4031 	return curLoop;
4032 };

4034 Sizzle.error = function( msg ) {
4035 	throw "Syntax error, unrecognized expression: " + msg;
4036 };

4444 			var type = match[1],

4448 				case "only":
4449 				case "first":
4450 					while ( (node = node.previousSibling) )	 {
4451 						if ( node.nodeType === 1 ) { 
4452 							return false; 
4453 						}
4454 					}
4455 
4456 					if ( type === "first" ) { 
4457 						return true; 
4458 					}
4459 
4460 					node = elem;
4461 
4462 				case "last":
4463 					while ( (node = node.nextSibling) )	 {
4464 						if ( node.nodeType === 1 ) { 
4465 							return false; 
4466 						}
4467 					}
4468 
4469 					return true;
4470 
4471 				case "nth":
4472 					var first = match[2],
4473 						last = match[3];
4474 
4475 					if ( first === 1 && last === 0 ) {
4476 						return true;
4477 					}

4480 						parent = elem.parentNode;
4481 	
4482 					if ( parent && (parent.sizcache !== doneName || !elem.nodeIndex) ) {
4483 						var count = 0;
4484 						
4485 						for ( node = parent.firstChild; node; node = node.nextSibling ) {
4486 							if ( node.nodeType === 1 ) {
4487 								node.nodeIndex = ++count;
4488 							}
4489 						} 
4490 
4491 						parent.sizcache = doneName;
4492 					}
4493 					
4494 					var diff = elem.nodeIndex - last;
4495 
4496 					if ( first === 0 ) {
4497 						return diff === 0;
4498 
4499 					} else {
4500 						return ( diff % first === 0 && diff / first >= 0 );
4501 					}
4502 			}

4506 			return elem.nodeType === 1 && elem.getAttribute("id") === match;
4507 		},

4511 		},

4513 		CLASS: function( elem, match ) {
4514 			return (" " + (elem.className || elem.getAttribute("class")) + " ")
4515 				.indexOf( match ) > -1;
4516 		},
4517 
4518 		ATTR: function( elem, match ) {
4519 			var name = match[1],
4520 				result = Expr.attrHandle[ name ] ?
4521 					Expr.attrHandle[ name ]( elem ) :
4522 					elem[ name ] != null ?
4523 						elem[ name ] :
4524 						elem.getAttribute( name ),
4525 				value = result + "",
4526 				type = match[2],
4527 				check = match[4];
4528 
4529 			return result == null ?
4530 				type === "!=" :
4531 				type === "=" ?
4532 				value === check :
4533 				type === "*=" ?
4534 				value.indexOf(check) >= 0 :
4535 				type === "~=" ?
4536 				(" " + value + " ").indexOf(check) >= 0 :
4537 				!check ?
4538 				value && result !== false :
4539 				type === "!=" ?
4540 				value !== check :
4541 				type === "^=" ?
4542 				value.indexOf(check) === 0 :
4543 				type === "$=" ?
4544 				value.substr(value.length - check.length) === check :
4545 				type === "|=" ?
4546 4547 				value === check || value.substr(0, check.length + 1) === check + "-" :
4548 				false;
4549 		},
4550 
4551 		POS: function( elem, match, i, array ) {
4552 			var name = match[2],
4553 				filter = Expr.setFilters[ name ];
4554 
4555 			if ( filter ) {
4556 				return filter( elem, i, match, array );
4557 			}
4558 		}
4559 	}

4563 	fescape = function(all, num){
4564 		return "\\" + (num - 0 + 1);

4568 	Expr.match[ type ] = new RegExp( Expr.match[ type ].source + (/(?![^\[]*\])(?![^\(]*\))/.source) );
4569 	Expr.leftMatch[ type ] = new RegExp( /(^(?:.|\r|\n)*?)/.source + Expr.match[ type ].source.replace(/\\(\d+)/g, fescape) );
4570 }
