4572 var makeArray = function( array, results ) {
4573 	array = Array.prototype.slice.call( array, 0 );
4574 
4575 	if ( results ) {
4576 		results.push.apply( results, array );
4577 		return results;
4578 	}
4579 	
4580 	return array;
4581 };

4583 // Perform a simple check to determine if the browser is capable of
4584 // converting a NodeList to an array using builtin methods.
4585 // Also verifies that the returned array holds DOM nodes
4586 // (which is not the case in the Blackberry browser)
4587 try {
4588 	Array.prototype.slice.call( document.documentElement.childNodes, 0 )[0].nodeType;
4589 
4590 // Provide a fallback method if it does not work
4591 } catch( e ) {
4592 	makeArray = function( array, results ) {
4593 		var i = 0,
4594 			ret = results || [];
4595 
4596 		if ( toString.call(array) === "[object Array]" ) {
4597 			Array.prototype.push.apply( ret, array );
4598 
4599 		} else {
4600 			if ( typeof array.length === "number" ) {
4601 				for ( var l = array.length; i < l; i++ ) {
4602 					ret.push( array[i] );
4603 				}
4604 
4605 			} else {
4606 				for ( ; array[i]; i++ ) {
4607 					ret.push( array[i] );
4608 				}
4609 			}
4610 		}
4611 
4612 		return ret;
4613 	};
4614 }
4615 
4616 var sortOrder, siblingCheck;
4617 
4618 if ( document.documentElement.compareDocumentPosition ) {
4619 	sortOrder = function( a, b ) {
4620 		if ( a === b ) {
4621 			hasDuplicate = true;
4622 			return 0;
4623 		}
4624 
4625 		if ( !a.compareDocumentPosition || !b.compareDocumentPosition ) {
4626 			return a.compareDocumentPosition ? -1 : 1;
4627 		}
4628 
4629 		return a.compareDocumentPosition(b) & 4 ? -1 : 1;
4630 	};
4631 
4632 } else {
4633 	sortOrder = function( a, b ) {
4634 		// The nodes are identical, we can exit early
4635 		if ( a === b ) {
4636 			hasDuplicate = true;
4637 			return 0;
4638 
4639 		// Fallback to using sourceIndex (in IE) if it's available on both nodes
4640 		} else if ( a.sourceIndex && b.sourceIndex ) {
4641 			return a.sourceIndex - b.sourceIndex;
4642 		}
4643 
4644 		var al, bl,
4645 			ap = [],
4646 			bp = [],
4647 			aup = a.parentNode,
4648 			bup = b.parentNode,
4649 			cur = aup;
4650 
4651 		// If the nodes are siblings (or identical) we can do a quick check
4652 		if ( aup === bup ) {
4653 			return siblingCheck( a, b );
4654 
4655 		// If no parents were found then the nodes are disconnected
4656 		} else if ( !aup ) {
4657 			return -1;
4658 
4659 		} else if ( !bup ) {
4660 			return 1;
4661 		}
4662 
4663 		// Otherwise they're somewhere else in the tree so we need
4664 		// to build up a full list of the parentNodes for comparison
4665 		while ( cur ) {
4666 			ap.unshift( cur );
4667 			cur = cur.parentNode;
4668 		}
4669 
4670 		cur = bup;
4671 
4672 		while ( cur ) {
4673 			bp.unshift( cur );
4674 			cur = cur.parentNode;
4675 		}
4676 
4677 		al = ap.length;
4678 		bl = bp.length;
4679 
4680 		// Start walking down the tree looking for a discrepancy
4681 		for ( var i = 0; i < al && i < bl; i++ ) {
4682 			if ( ap[i] !== bp[i] ) {
4683 				return siblingCheck( ap[i], bp[i] );
4684 			}
4685 		}
4686 
4687 		// We ended someplace up the tree so do a sibling check
4688 		return i === al ?
4689 			siblingCheck( a, bp[i], -1 ) :
4690 			siblingCheck( ap[i], b, 1 );
4691 	};
4692 
4693 	siblingCheck = function( a, b, ret ) {
4694 		if ( a === b ) {
4695 			return ret;
4696 		}
4697 
4698 		var cur = a.nextSibling;
4699 
4700 		while ( cur ) {
4701 			if ( cur === b ) {
4702 				return -1;
4703 			}
4704 
4705 			cur = cur.nextSibling;
4706 		}
4707 
4708 		return 1;
4709 	};
4710 }

4712 // Utility function for retreiving the text value of an array of DOM nodes
4713 Sizzle.getText = function( elems ) {
4714 	var ret = "", elem;
4715 
4716 	for ( var i = 0; elems[i]; i++ ) {
4717 		elem = elems[i];
4718 
4719 		// Get the text from text nodes and CDATA nodes
4720 		if ( elem.nodeType === 3 || elem.nodeType === 4 ) {
4721 			ret += elem.nodeValue;
4722 
4723 		// Traverse everything else, except comment nodes
4724 		} else if ( elem.nodeType !== 8 ) {
4725 			ret += Sizzle.getText( elem.childNodes );
4726 		}
4727 	}
4728 
4729 	return ret;
4730 };

4833 			context = context || document;
4834 
4835 			// Only use querySelectorAll on non-XML documents
4836 			// (ID selectors don't work in non-HTML documents)
4837 			if ( !seed && !Sizzle.isXML(context) ) {
4838 				// See if we find a selector to speed up
4839 				var match = /^(\w+$)|^\.([\w\-]+$)|^#([\w\-]+$)/.exec( query );
4840 				
4841 				if ( match && (context.nodeType === 1 || context.nodeType === 9) ) {
4842 					// Speed-up: Sizzle("TAG")
4843 					if ( match[1] ) {
4844 						return makeArray( context.getElementsByTagName( query ), extra );
4845 					
4846 					// Speed-up: Sizzle(".CLASS")
4847 					} else if ( match[2] && Expr.find.CLASS && context.getElementsByClassName ) {
4848 						return makeArray( context.getElementsByClassName( match[2] ), extra );

4853 					// Speed-up: Sizzle("body")
4854 					// The body element only exists once, optimize finding it
4855 					if ( query === "body" && context.body ) {
4856 						return makeArray( [ context.body ], extra );
4857 						
4858 					// Speed-up: Sizzle("#ID")
4859 					} else if ( match && match[3] ) {

4870

4872 							return makeArray( [], extra );
4873 						}

4880 				// qSA works strangely on Element-rooted queries
4881 				// We can work around this by specifying an extra ID on the root
4882 				// and working up from there (Thanks to Andrew Dupont for the technique)
4883 				// IE 8 doesn't work on object elements
4884 				} else if ( context.nodeType === 1 && context.nodeName.toLowerCase() !== "object" ) {

4886 						old = context.getAttribute( "id" ),

4889 						relativeHierarchySelector = /^\s*[+~]/.test( query );

4893 					} else {

4895 					}

4897 						context = context.parentNode;

4900 					try {
4901 						if ( !relativeHierarchySelector || hasParent ) {
4902 							return makeArray( context.querySelectorAll( "[id='" + nid + "'] " + query ), extra );
4903 						}
4904 
4905 					} catch(pseudoError) {
4906 					} finally {
4907 						if ( !old ) {
4908 							oldContext.removeAttribute( "id" );
4909 						}
4910 					}
4911 				}
4912 			}

4915 		};

4999 function dirNodeCheck( dir, cur, doneName, checkSet, nodeCheck, isXML ) {
5000 	for ( var i = 0, l = checkSet.length; i < l; i++ ) {
5001 		var elem = checkSet[i];
5002 
5003 		if ( elem ) {
5004 			var match = false;
5005 
5006 			elem = elem[dir];
5007 
5008 			while ( elem ) {
5009 				if ( elem.sizcache === doneName ) {
5010 					match = checkSet[elem.sizset];
5011 					break;
5012 				}
5013 
5014 				if ( elem.nodeType === 1 && !isXML ){
5015 					elem.sizcache = doneName;
5016 					elem.sizset = i;
5017 				}
5018 
5019 				if ( elem.nodeName.toLowerCase() === cur ) {
5020 					match = elem;
5021 					break;
5022 				}
5023 
5024 				elem = elem[dir];
5025 			}
5026 
5027 			checkSet[i] = match;
5028 		}
5029 	}
5030 }

5032 function dirCheck( dir, cur, doneName, checkSet, nodeCheck, isXML ) {
5033 	for ( var i = 0, l = checkSet.length; i < l; i++ ) {
5034 		var elem = checkSet[i];
5035 
5036 		if ( elem ) {
5037 			var match = false;
5038 			
5039 			elem = elem[dir];
5040 
5041 			while ( elem ) {
5042 				if ( elem.sizcache === doneName ) {
5043 					match = checkSet[elem.sizset];
5044 					break;
5045 				}
5046 
5047 				if ( elem.nodeType === 1 ) {
5048 					if ( !isXML ) {
5049 						elem.sizcache = doneName;
5050 						elem.sizset = i;
5051 					}
5052 
5053 					if ( typeof cur !== "string" ) {
5054 						if ( elem === cur ) {
5055 							match = true;
5056 							break;
5057 						}
5058 
5059 					} else if ( Sizzle.filter( cur, [elem] ).length > 0 ) {
5060 						match = elem;
5061 						break;
5062 					}
5063 				}
5064 
5065 				elem = elem[dir];
5066 			}
5067 
5068 			checkSet[i] = match;
5069 		}
5070 	}

var posProcess = function( selector, context ) {
5098 	var match,
5099 		tmpSet = [],
5100 		later = "",
5101 		root = context.nodeType ? [context] : context;
5102 
5103 	// Position selectors must be done after the filter
5104 	// And so must :not(positional) so we move all PSEUDOs to the end
5105 	while ( (match = Expr.match.PSEUDO.exec( selector )) ) {
5106 		later += match[0];
5107 		selector = selector.replace( Expr.match.PSEUDO, "" );
5108 	}
5109 
5110 	selector = Expr.relative[selector] ? selector + "*" : selector;
5111 
5112 	for ( var i = 0, l = root.length; i < l; i++ ) {
5113 		Sizzle( selector, root[i], tmpSet );
5114 	}
5115 
5116 	return Sizzle.filter( later, tmpSet );
5117 };

5210 	closest: function( selectors, context ) {
5211 		var ret = [], i, l, cur = this[0];
5212 		
5213 		// Array
5214 		if ( jQuery.isArray( selectors ) ) {
5215 			var match, selector,
5216 				matches = {},
5217 				level = 1;
5218

5220 				for ( i = 0, l = selectors.length; i < l; i++ ) {
5221 					selector = selectors[i];
5222

5224 						matches[ selector ] = POS.test( selector ) ?
5225 							jQuery( selector, context || this.context ) :
5226 							selector;

5230 				while ( cur && cur.ownerDocument && cur !== context ) {
5231 					for ( selector in matches ) {
5232 						match = matches[ selector ];
5233 
5234 						if ( match.jquery ? match.index( cur ) > -1 : jQuery( cur ).is( match ) ) {
5235 							ret.push({ selector: selector, elem: cur, level: level });
5236 						}
5237 					}
5238 
5239 					cur = cur.parentNode;
5240 					level++;
5241 				}
5242 			}
5243 
5244 			return ret;
5245 		}
5246 
5247 		// String
5248 		var pos = POS.test( selectors ) || typeof selectors !== "string" ?
5249 				jQuery( selectors, context || this.context ) :
5250 				0;
5251 
5252 		for ( i = 0, l = this.length; i < l; i++ ) {
5253 			cur = this[i];
5254 
5255 			while ( cur ) {
5256 				if ( pos ? pos.index(cur) > -1 : jQuery.find.matchesSelector(cur, selectors) ) {
5257 					ret.push( cur );
5258 					break;
5259 
5260 				} else {
5261 					cur = cur.parentNode;
5262 					if ( !cur || !cur.ownerDocument || cur === context || cur.nodeType === 11 ) {
5263 						break;
5264 					}
5265 				}
5266 			}
5267 		}
5268 
5269 		ret = ret.length > 1 ? jQuery.unique( ret ) : ret;
5270 
5271 		return this.pushStack( ret, "closest", selectors );
5272 	},
5273 
5274 	// Determine the position of an element within
5275 	// the matched set of elements
5276 	index: function( elem ) {
5277 		if ( !elem || typeof elem === "string" ) {
5278 			return jQuery.inArray( this[0],
5279 				// If it receives a string, the selector is used
5280 				// If it receives nothing, the siblings are used
5281 				elem ? jQuery( elem ) : this.parent().children() );
5282 		}
5283 		// Locate the position of the desired element
5284 		return jQuery.inArray(
5285 			// If it receives a jQuery object, the first element is used
5286 			elem.jquery ? elem[0] : elem, this );
5287 	},
5288

5292 				jQuery.makeArray( selector && selector.nodeType ? [ selector ] : selector ),
5293 			all = jQuery.merge( this.get(), set );
5294 
5295 		return this.pushStack( isDisconnected( set[0] ) || isDisconnected( all[0] ) ?
5296 			all :
5297 			jQuery.unique( all ) );

5428 // Implement the identical functionality for filter and not
5429 function winnow( elements, qualifier, keep ) {
5430 
5431 	// Can't pass null or undefined to indexOf in Firefox 4
5432 	// Set to 0 to skip string check
5433 	qualifier = qualifier || 0;
5434 
5435 	if ( jQuery.isFunction( qualifier ) ) {
5436 		return jQuery.grep(elements, function( elem, i ) {
5437 			var retVal = !!qualifier.call( elem, i, elem );
5438 			return retVal === keep;
5439 		});
5440 
5441 	} else if ( qualifier.nodeType ) {
5442 		return jQuery.grep(elements, function( elem, i ) {
5443 			return (elem === qualifier) === keep;
5444 		});
5445 
5446 	} else if ( typeof qualifier === "string" ) {
5447 		var filtered = jQuery.grep(elements, function( elem ) {
5448 			return elem.nodeType === 1;
5449 		});
5450 
5451 		if ( isSimple.test( qualifier ) ) {
5452 			return jQuery.filter(qualifier, filtered, !keep);
5453 		} else {
5454 			qualifier = jQuery.filter( qualifier, filtered );
5455 		}
5456 	}
5457 
5458 	return jQuery.grep(elements, function( elem, i ) {
5459 		return (jQuery.inArray( elem, qualifier ) >= 0) === keep;
5460 	});
5461 }

5704 			// this can help fix replacing a parent with child elements
5705 			if ( jQuery.isFunction( value ) ) {
5706 				return this.each(function(i) {
5707 					var self = jQuery(this), old = self.html();
5708 					self.replaceWith( value.call( this, i, old ) );
5709 				});
5710 			}

5712 			if ( typeof value !== "string" ) {
5713 				value = jQuery( value ).detach();
5714 			}

5717 5718 				var next = this.nextSibling,

5729 		} else {

5740 	domManip: function( args, table, callback ) {
5741 		var results, first, fragment, parent,
5742 			value = args[0],
5743 			scripts = [];
5744 
5745 		// We can't cloneNode fragments that contain checked, in WebKit
5746 		if ( !jQuery.support.checkClone && arguments.length === 3 && typeof value === "string" && rchecked.test( value ) ) {
5747 			return this.each(function() {
5748 				jQuery(this).domManip( args, table, callback, true );
5749 			});
5750 		}
5751 
5752 		if ( jQuery.isFunction(value) ) {
5753 			return this.each(function(i) {
5754 				var self = jQuery(this);
5755 				args[0] = value.call(this, i, table ? self.html() : undefined);
5756 				self.domManip( args, table, callback );
5757 			});
5758 		}
5759 
5760 		if ( this[0] ) {
5761 			parent = value && value.parentNode;
5762 
5763 5764 			// If we're in a fragment, just use that instead of building a new one
5765 			if ( jQuery.support.parentNode && parent && parent.nodeType === 11 && parent.childNodes.length === this.length ) {
5766 				results = { fragment: parent };
5767 
5768 			} else {
5769 				results = jQuery.buildFragment( args, this, scripts );
5770 			}
5771 
5772 			fragment = results.fragment;
5773 
5774 			if ( fragment.childNodes.length === 1 ) {
5775 				first = fragment = fragment.firstChild;
5776 			} else {
5777 				first = fragment.firstChild;
5778 			}
5779 
5780 			if ( first ) {
5781 				table = table && jQuery.nodeName( first, "tr" );
5782 
5783 				for ( var i = 0, l = this.length, lastIndex = l - 1; i < l; i++ ) {
5784 					callback.call(
5785 						table ?
5786 							root(this[i], first) :
5787 							this[i],
5788 						// Make sure that we do not leak memory by inadvertently discarding
5789 						// the original fragment (which might have attached data) instead of
5790 						// using it; in addition, use the original fragment object for the last
5791 						// item instead of first because it can end up being emptied incorrectly
5792 						// in certain situations (Bug #8070).
5793 						// Fragments from the fragment cache must always be cloned and never used
5794 						// in place.
5795 						results.cacheable || (l > 1 && i < lastIndex) ?
5796 							jQuery.clone( fragment, true, true ) :
5797 							fragment
5798 					);
5799 				}
5800 			}
5801 
5802 			if ( scripts.length ) {
5803 				jQuery.each( scripts, evalScript );
5804 			}
5805 		}
5806 
5807 		return this;
5808 	}
5809 });

5813 		(elem.getElementsByTagName("tbody")[0] ||
5814 		elem.appendChild(elem.ownerDocument.createElement("tbody"))) :
5815 		elem;
5816 }

5818 function cloneCopyEvent( src, dest ) {
5819 
5820 	if ( dest.nodeType !== 1 || !jQuery.hasData( src ) ) {
5821 		return;
5822 	}
5823 
5824 	var internalKey = jQuery.expando,
5825 		oldData = jQuery.data( src ),
5826 		curData = jQuery.data( dest, oldData );
5827 
5828 	// Switch to use the internal data object, if it exists, for the next
5829 	// stage of data copying
5830 	if ( (oldData = oldData[ internalKey ]) ) {
5831 		var events = oldData.events;
5832 				curData = curData[ internalKey ] = jQuery.extend({}, oldData);
5833 
5834 		if ( events ) {
5835 			delete curData.handle;
5836 			curData.events = {};
5837 
5838 			for ( var type in events ) {
5839 				for ( var i = 0, l = events[ type ].length; i < l; i++ ) {
5840 					jQuery.event.add( dest, type + ( events[ type ][ i ].namespace ? "." : "" ) + events[ type ][ i ].namespace, events[ type ][ i ], events[ type ][ i ].data );
5841 				}
5842 			}
5843 		}
5844 	}
5845 }
5846 
5847 function cloneFixAttributes( src, dest ) {
5848 	var nodeName;
5849 
5850 	// We do not need to do anything for non-Elements
5851 	if ( dest.nodeType !== 1 ) {
5852 		return;
5853 	}
5854 
5855 	// clearAttributes removes the attributes, which we don't want,
5856 	// but also removes the attachEvent events, which we *do* want
5857 	if ( dest.clearAttributes ) {
5858 		dest.clearAttributes();
5859 	}
5860 
5861 	// mergeAttributes, in contrast, only merges back on the
5862 	// original attributes, not the events
5863 	if ( dest.mergeAttributes ) {
5864 		dest.mergeAttributes( src );
5865 	}
5866 
5867 	nodeName = dest.nodeName.toLowerCase();
5868 
5869 	// IE6-8 fail to clone children inside object elements that use
5870 	// the proprietary classid attribute value (rather than the type
5871 	// attribute) to identify the type of content to display
5872 	if ( nodeName === "object" ) {
5873 		dest.outerHTML = src.outerHTML;
5874 
5875 	} else if ( nodeName === "input" && (src.type === "checkbox" || src.type === "radio") ) {
5876 		// IE6-8 fails to persist the checked state of a cloned checkbox
5877 		// or radio button. Worse, IE6-7 fail to give the cloned element
5878 		// a checked appearance if the defaultChecked value isn't also set
5879 		if ( src.checked ) {
5880 			dest.defaultChecked = dest.checked = src.checked;
5881 		}
5882 
5883 		// IE6-7 get confused and end up setting the value of a cloned
5884 		// checkbox/radio button to an empty string instead of "on"
5885 		if ( dest.value !== src.value ) {
5886 			dest.value = src.value;
5887 		}
5888 
5889 	// IE6-8 fails to return the selected option to the default selected
5890 	// state when cloning options
5891 	} else if ( nodeName === "option" ) {
5892 		dest.selected = src.defaultSelected;
5893 
5894 	// IE6-8 fails to set the defaultValue to the correct value when
5895 	// cloning other types of input fields
5896 	} else if ( nodeName === "input" || nodeName === "textarea" ) {
5897 		dest.defaultValue = src.defaultValue;
5898 	}
5899 
5900 	// Event data gets referenced instead of copied if the expando
5901 	// gets copied too
5902 	dest.removeAttribute( jQuery.expando );
5903 }
5904 
5905 jQuery.buildFragment = function( args, nodes, scripts ) {
5906 	var fragment, cacheable, cacheresults,
5907 		doc = (nodes && nodes[0] ? nodes[0].ownerDocument || nodes[0] : document);
5908 
5909 	// Only cache "small" (1/2 KB) HTML strings that are associated with the main document
5910 	// Cloning options loses the selected state, so don't cache them
5911 	// IE 6 doesn't like it when you put <object> or <embed> elements in a fragment
5912 	// Also, WebKit does not clone 'checked' attributes on cloneNode, so don't cache
5913 	if ( args.length === 1 && typeof args[0] === "string" && args[0].length < 512 && doc === document &&
5914 		args[0].charAt(0) === "<" && !rnocache.test( args[0] ) && (jQuery.support.checkClone || !rchecked.test( args[0] )) ) {
5915 
5916 		cacheable = true;
5917 
5918 		cacheresults = jQuery.fragments[ args[0] ];
5919 		if ( cacheresults && cacheresults !== 1 ) {
5920 			fragment = cacheresults;
5921 		}
5922 	}
5923 
5924 	if ( !fragment ) {
5925 		fragment = doc.createDocumentFragment();
5926 		jQuery.clean( args, doc, fragment, scripts );
5927 	}
5928 
5929 	if ( cacheable ) {
5930 		jQuery.fragments[ args[0] ] = cacheresults ? fragment : 1;
5931 	}
5932 
5933 	return { fragment: fragment, cacheable: cacheable };
5934 };

5938 jQuery.each({
5939 	appendTo: "append",
5940 	prependTo: "prepend",
5941 	insertBefore: "before",
5942 5943 	insertAfter: "after",
5944 	replaceAll: "replaceWith"
5945 }, function( name, original ) {
5946 	jQuery.fn[ name ] = function( selector ) {
5947 		var ret = [],
5948 			insert = jQuery( selector ),
5949 			parent = this.length === 1 && this[0].parentNode;
5950 
5951 		if ( parent && parent.nodeType === 11 && parent.childNodes.length === 1 && insert.length === 1 ) {
5952 			insert[ original ]( this[0] );
5953 			return this;
5954 
5955 		} else {
5956 			for ( var i = 0, l = insert.length; i < l; i++ ) {
5957 				var elems = (i > 0 ? this.clone(true) : this).get();
5958 				jQuery( insert[i] )[ original ]( elems );
5959 				ret = ret.concat( elems );
5960 			}
5961 
5962 			return this.pushStack( ret, name, insert.selector );
5963 		}
5964 	};

5967 function getAll( elem ) {
5968 	if ( "getElementsByTagName" in elem ) {
5969 		return elem.getElementsByTagName( "*" );
5970 
5971 	} else if ( "querySelectorAll" in elem ) {
5972 		return elem.querySelectorAll( "*" );
5973 
5974 	} else {
5975 		return [];
5976 	}
5977 }

5979 // Used in clean, fixes the defaultChecked property
5980 function fixDefaultChecked( elem ) {
5981 	if ( elem.type === "checkbox" || elem.type === "radio" ) {
5982 		elem.defaultChecked = elem.checked;
5983 	}
5984 }
5985 // Finds all inputs and passes them to fixDefaultChecked
5986 function findInputs( elem ) {
5987 	if ( jQuery.nodeName( elem, "input" ) ) {
5988 		fixDefaultChecked( elem );
5989 	} else if ( elem.getElementsByTagName ) {
5990 		jQuery.grep( elem.getElementsByTagName("input"), fixDefaultChecked );
5991 	}
5992 }

5994 jQuery.extend({
5995 	clone: function( elem, dataAndEvents, deepDataAndEvents ) {
5996 		var clone = elem.cloneNode(true),
5997 				srcElements,
5998 				destElements,
5999 				i;
6000 
6001 		if ( (!jQuery.support.noCloneEvent || !jQuery.support.noCloneChecked) &&
6002 				(elem.nodeType === 1 || elem.nodeType === 11) && !jQuery.isXMLDoc(elem) ) {
6003 			// IE copies events bound via attachEvent when using cloneNode.
6004 			// Calling detachEvent on the clone will also remove the events
6005 			// from the original. In order to get around this, we use some
6006 			// proprietary methods to clear the events. Thanks to MooTools
6007 			// guys for this hotness.
6008 
6009 			cloneFixAttributes( elem, clone );
6010 
6011 			// Using Sizzle here is crazy slow, so we use getElementsByTagName
6012 			// instead
6013 			srcElements = getAll( elem );
6014 			destElements = getAll( clone );
6015 
6016 			// Weird iteration because IE will replace the length property
6017 			// with an element if you are cloning the body and one of the
6018 			// elements on the page has a name or id of "length"
6019 			for ( i = 0; srcElements[i]; ++i ) {
6020 				cloneFixAttributes( srcElements[i], destElements[i] );
6021 			}
6022 		}
6023 
6024 		// Copy the events from the original to the clone
6025 		if ( dataAndEvents ) {
6026 			cloneCopyEvent( elem, clone );
6027 
6028 			if ( deepDataAndEvents ) {
6029 				srcElements = getAll( elem );
6030 				destElements = getAll( clone );
6031 6032 
				for ( i = 0; srcElements[i]; ++i ) {
6033 					cloneCopyEvent( srcElements[i], destElements[i] );
6034 				}
6035 			}
6036 		}
6037 
6038 		// Return the cloned set
6039 		return clone;
6040 	},
6041 
6042 	clean: function( elems, context, fragment, scripts ) {
6043 		var checkScriptType;
6044 
6045 		context = context || document;
6046 
6047 		// !context.createElement fails in IE with an error but returns typeof 'object'
6048 		if ( typeof context.createElement === "undefined" ) {
6049 			context = context.ownerDocument || context[0] && context[0].ownerDocument || document;
6050 		}
6051 
6052 		var ret = [], j;
6053 
6054 		for ( var i = 0, elem; (elem = elems[i]) != null; i++ ) {
6055 			if ( typeof elem === "number" ) {
6056 				elem += "";
6057 			}
6058 
6059 			if ( !elem ) {
6060 				continue;
6061 			}
6062 
6063 			// Convert html string into DOM nodes
6064 			if ( typeof elem === "string" ) {
6065 				if ( !rhtml.test( elem ) ) {
6066 					elem = context.createTextNode( elem );
6067 				} else {
6068 					// Fix "XHTML"-style tags in all browsers
6069 					elem = elem.replace(rxhtmlTag, "<$1></$2>");
6070 
6071 					// Trim whitespace, otherwise indexOf won't work as expected
6072 					var tag = (rtagName.exec( elem ) || ["", ""])[1].toLowerCase(),
6073 						wrap = wrapMap[ tag ] || wrapMap._default,
6074 						depth = wrap[0],
6075 						div = context.createElement("div");
6076 
6077 					// Go to html and back, then peel off extra wrappers
6078 					div.innerHTML = wrap[1] + elem + wrap[2];
6079 
6080 					// Move to the right depth
6081 					while ( depth-- ) {
6082 						div = div.lastChild;
6083 					}
6084 
6085 					// Remove IE's autoinserted <tbody> from table fragments
6086 					if ( !jQuery.support.tbody ) {
6087 
6088 						// String was a <table>, *may* have spurious <tbody>
6089 						var hasBody = rtbody.test(elem),
6090 							tbody = tag === "table" && !hasBody ?
6091 								div.firstChild && div.firstChild.childNodes :
6092 
6093 								// String was a bare <thead> or <tfoot>
6094 								wrap[1] === "<table>" && !hasBody ?
6095 									div.childNodes :
6096 									[];
6097 
6098 						for ( j = tbody.length - 1; j >= 0 ; --j ) {
6099 							if ( jQuery.nodeName( tbody[ j ], "tbody" ) && !tbody[ j ].childNodes.length ) {
6100 								tbody[ j ].parentNode.removeChild( tbody[ j ] );
6101 							}
6102 						}
6103 					}
6104 
6105 					// IE completely kills leading whitespace when innerHTML is used
6106 					if ( !jQuery.support.leadingWhitespace && rleadingWhitespace.test( elem ) ) {
6107 						div.insertBefore( context.createTextNode( rleadingWhitespace.exec(elem)[0] ), div.firstChild );
6108 					}
6109 
6110 					elem = div.childNodes;
6111 				}
6112 			}
6113 
6114 			// Resets defaultChecked for any radios and checkboxes
6115 			// about to be appended to the DOM in IE 6/7 (#8060)
6116 			var len;
6117 			if ( !jQuery.support.appendChecked ) {
6118 				if ( elem[0] && typeof (len = elem.length) === "number" ) {
6119 					for ( j = 0; j < len; j++ ) {
6120 						findInputs( elem[j] );
6121 					}
6122 				} else {
6123 					findInputs( elem );
6124 				}
6125 			}
6126 
6127 			if ( elem.nodeType ) {
6128 				ret.push( elem );
6129 			} else {
6130 				ret = jQuery.merge( ret, elem );
6131 			}
6132 		}
6133 
6134 		if ( fragment ) {
6135 			checkScriptType = function( elem ) {
6136 				return !elem.type || rscriptType.test( elem.type );
6137 			};
6138 			for ( i = 0; ret[i]; i++ ) {
6139 				if ( scripts && jQuery.nodeName( ret[i], "script" ) && (!ret[i].type || ret[i].type.toLowerCase() === "text/javascript") ) {
6140 					scripts.push( ret[i].parentNode ? ret[i].parentNode.removeChild( ret[i] ) : ret[i] );
6141 
6142 				} else {
6143 					if ( ret[i].nodeType === 1 ) {
6144 						var jsTags = jQuery.grep( ret[i].getElementsByTagName( "script" ), checkScriptType );
6145 
6146 						ret.splice.apply( ret, [i + 1, 0].concat( jsTags ) );
6147 					}
6148 					fragment.appendChild( ret[i] );
6149 				}
6150 			}
6151 		}
6152 
6153 		return ret;
6154 	},
6155 
6156 	cleanData: function( elems ) {
6157 6158 		var data, id, cache = jQuery.cache, internalKey = jQuery.expando, special = jQuery.event.special,
6159 			deleteExpando = jQuery.support.deleteExpando;
6160 
6161 		for ( var i = 0, elem; (elem = elems[i]) != null; i++ ) {
6162 			if ( elem.nodeName && jQuery.noData[elem.nodeName.toLowerCase()] ) {
6163 				continue;
6164 			}
6165 
6166 			id = elem[ jQuery.expando ];
6167 
6168 			if ( id ) {
6169 				data = cache[ id ] && cache[ id ][ internalKey ];
6170 
6171 				if ( data && data.events ) {
6172 					for ( var type in data.events ) {
6173 						if ( special[ type ] ) {
6174 							jQuery.event.remove( elem, type );
6175 
6176 						// This is a shortcut to avoid jQuery.event.remove's overhead
6177 						} else {
6178 							jQuery.removeEvent( elem, type, data.handle );
6179 						}
6180 					}
6181 
6182 					// Null the DOM reference to avoid IE6/7/8 leak (#7054)
6183 					if ( data.handle ) {
6184 						data.handle.elem = null;
6185 					}
6186 				}
6187 
6188 				if ( deleteExpando ) {
6189 					delete elem[ jQuery.expando ];
6190 
6191 				} else if ( elem.removeAttribute ) {
6192 					elem.removeAttribute( jQuery.expando );
6193 				}
6194 
6195 				delete cache[ id ];
6196 			}
6197 		}
6198 	}
6199 });

6201 function evalScript( i, elem ) {
6202 	if ( elem.src ) {
6203 		jQuery.ajax({
6204 			url: elem.src,
6205 			async: false,
6206 			dataType: "script"
6207 		});
6208 	} else {
6209 		jQuery.globalEval( ( elem.text || elem.textContent || elem.innerHTML || "" ).replace( rcleanScript, "/*$0*/" ) );
6210 	}
6211 
6212 	if ( elem.parentNode ) {
6213 		elem.parentNode.removeChild( elem );
6214 	}
6215 }

6242 jQuery.fn.css = function( name, value ) {

6245 		return this;
6246 	}

6252 	});

6255 jQuery.extend({
6256 	// Add in style property hooks for overriding the default
6257 	// behavior of getting and setting a style property
6258 	cssHooks: {
6259 		opacity: {
6260 			get: function( elem, computed ) {
6261 				if ( computed ) {
6262 					// We should always get a number back from opacity
6263 					var ret = curCSS( elem, "opacity", "opacity" );
6264 					return ret === "" ? "1" : ret;
6265

6267 					return elem.style.opacity;
6268 				}

6274 	// Exclude the following css properties to add px
6275 	cssNumber: {
6276 		"zIndex": true,
6277 		"fontWeight": true,
6278 		"opacity": true,
6279 		"zoom": true,
6280 		"lineHeight": true,
6281 		"widows": true,
6282 		"orphans": true
6283 	},
6284 
6285 	// Add in properties whose names you wish to fix before
6286 	// setting or getting the value
6287 	cssProps: {
6288 		// normalize float css property
6289 		"float": jQuery.support.cssFloat ? "cssFloat" : "styleFloat"
6290 	},

6292 	// Get and set the style property on a DOM Node
6293 	style: function( elem, name, value, extra ) {
6294 		// Don't set styles on text and comment nodes
6295 		if ( !elem || elem.nodeType === 3 || elem.nodeType === 8 || !elem.style ) {
6296 			return;
6297 		}
6298 
6299 		// Make sure that we're working with the right name
6300 		var ret, type, origName = jQuery.camelCase( name ),
6301 			style = elem.style, hooks = jQuery.cssHooks[ origName ];
6302 
6303 		name = jQuery.cssProps[ origName ] || origName;
6304 
6305 		// Check if we're setting a value
6306 		if ( value !== undefined ) {
6307 			type = typeof value;
6308 
6309 			// Make sure that NaN and null values aren't set. See: #7116
6310 			if ( type === "number" && isNaN( value ) || value == null ) {
6311 				return;
6312 			}
6313 
6314 			// convert relative number strings (+= or -=) to relative numbers. #7345
6315 			if ( type === "string" && rrelNum.test( value ) ) {
6316 				value = +value.replace( rrelNumFilter, "" ) + parseFloat( jQuery.css( elem, name ) );
6317 			}
6318 
6319 			// If a number was passed in, add 'px' to the (except for certain CSS properties)
6320 			if ( type === "number" && !jQuery.cssNumber[ origName ] ) {
6321 				value += "px";
6322 			}
6323 
6324 			// If a hook was provided, use that value, otherwise just set the specified value
6325 			if ( !hooks || !("set" in hooks) || (value = hooks.set( elem, value )) !== undefined ) {
6326 				// Wrapped to prevent IE from throwing errors when 'invalid' values are provided
6327 				// Fixes bug #5509
6328 				try {
6329 					style[ name ] = value;
6330 				} catch(e) {}
6331 			}
6332 
6333 		} else {
6334 			// If a hook was provided get the non-computed value from there
6335 			if ( hooks && "get" in hooks && (ret = hooks.get( elem, false, extra )) !== undefined ) {
6336 				return ret;
6337 			}
6338 
6339 			// Otherwise just get the value from the style object
6340 			return style[ name ];
6341 		}
6342 	},
6343 
6344 	css: function( elem, name, extra ) {
6345 		var ret, hooks;
6346 
6347 		// Make sure that we're working with the right name
6348 		name = jQuery.camelCase( name );
6349 		hooks = jQuery.cssHooks[ name ];
6350 		name = jQuery.cssProps[ name ] || name;
6351 
6352 		// cssFloat needs a special treatment
6353 		if ( name === "cssFloat" ) {
6354 			name = "float";
6355 		}
6356 
6357 		// If a hook was provided get the computed value from there
6358 		if ( hooks && "get" in hooks && (ret = hooks.get( elem, true, extra )) !== undefined ) {
6359 			return ret;
6360 
6361 		// Otherwise, if a way to get the computed value exists, use that
6362 		} else if ( curCSS ) {
6363 			return curCSS( elem, name );
6364 		}
6365 	},

6367 	// A method for quickly swapping in/out CSS properties to get correct calculations
6368 	swap: function( elem, options, callback ) {
6369 		var old = {};
6370 
6371 		// Remember the old values, and insert the new ones
6372 		for ( var name in options ) {
6373 			old[ name ] = elem.style[ name ];
6374 			elem.style[ name ] = options[ name ];
6375 		}
6376 
6377 		callback.call( elem );
6378 
6379 		// Revert the old values
6380 		for ( name in options ) {
6381 			elem.style[ name ] = old[ name ];
6382 		}
6383 	},

6393 jQuery.each(["height", "width"], function( i, name ) {

6396 			var val;

6400 					val = getWH( elem, name, extra );

6404 						val = getWH( elem, name, extra );

6410

6412 						val = currentStyle( elem, name, name );
6413 					}

6416 						// Should return "auto" instead of 0, use 0 for
6417 						// temporary backwards-compat
6418 						return val === "" || val === "auto" ? "0px" : val;
6419 					}
6420 				}
6421 
6422 				if ( val < 0 || val == null ) {
6423 					val = elem.style[ name ];
6424 
6425 					// Should return "auto" instead of 0, use 0 for
6426 					// temporary backwards-compat
6427 					return val === "" || val === "auto" ? "0px" : val;
6428 				}
6429 
6430 				return typeof val === "string" ? val : val + "px";
6431 			}

6456 				computed ? "1" : "";

6472

6502 if ( document.defaultView && document.defaultView.getComputedStyle ) {
6503 	getComputedStyle = function( elem, name ) {
6504 		var ret, defaultView, computedStyle;
6505 
6506 		name = name.replace( rupper, "-$1" ).toLowerCase();
6507

6509 			return undefined;
6510 		}

6513 			ret = computedStyle.getPropertyValue( name );
6514 			if ( ret === "" && !jQuery.contains( elem.ownerDocument.documentElement, elem ) ) {

6523 if ( document.documentElement.currentStyle ) {
6524 	currentStyle = function( elem, name ) {
6525 		var left,
6526 			ret = elem.currentStyle && elem.currentStyle[ name ],
6527 			rsLeft = elem.runtimeStyle && elem.runtimeStyle[ name ],
6528 			style = elem.style;
6529 
6530 		// From the awesome hack by Dean Edwards
6531 		// http://erik.eae.net/archives/2007/07/27/18.54.15/#comment-102291
6532 
6533 		// If we're not dealing with a regular pixel number
6534 		// but a number that has a weird ending, we need to convert it to pixels
6535 		if ( !rnumpx.test( ret ) && rnum.test( ret ) ) {
6536 			// Remember the original values
6537 			left = style.left;
6538 
6539 			// Put in the new values to get a computed value out
6540 			if ( rsLeft ) {
6541 				elem.runtimeStyle.left = elem.currentStyle.left;
6542 			}
6543 			style.left = name === "fontSize" ? "1em" : (ret || 0);
6544 			ret = style.pixelLeft + "px";
6545 
6546 			// Revert the changed values
6547 			style.left = left;
6548 			if ( rsLeft ) {
6549 				elem.runtimeStyle.left = rsLeft;
6550 			}
6551 		}
6552 
6553 		return ret === "" ? "auto" : ret;
6554 	};
6555 }

6559 function getWH( elem, name, extra ) {
6560 	var which = name === "width" ? cssWidth : cssHeight,
6561 		val = name === "width" ? elem.offsetWidth : elem.offsetHeight;
6562 
6563 	if ( extra === "border" ) {
6564 		return val;
6565 	}
6566 
6567 	jQuery.each( which, function() {
6568 		if ( !extra ) {
6569 			val -= parseFloat(jQuery.css( elem, "padding" + this )) || 0;
6570 		}
6571 
6572 		if ( extra === "margin" ) {
6573 			val += parseFloat(jQuery.css( elem, "margin" + this )) || 0;
6574 
6575 		} else {
6576 			val -= parseFloat(jQuery.css( elem, "border" + this + "Width" )) || 0;
6577 		}
6578 	});
6579 
6580 	return val;
6581 }

6621 	 * 2) These are called:
6622 	 *    - BEFORE asking for a transport
6623 	 *    - AFTER param serialization (s.data is a string if s.processData is true)

6626 	 * 5) execution will start with transport dataType and THEN continue down to "*" if needed
6627 	 */

6658 // Base "constructor" for jQuery.ajaxPrefilter and jQuery.ajaxTransport
6659 function addToPrefiltersOrTransports( structure ) {
6660 
6661 	// dataTypeExpression is optional and defaults to "*"
6662 	return function( dataTypeExpression, func ) {
6663 
6664 		if ( typeof dataTypeExpression !== "string" ) {
6665 			func = dataTypeExpression;
6666 			dataTypeExpression = "*";
6667 		}
6668 
6669 		if ( jQuery.isFunction( func ) ) {
6670 			var dataTypes = dataTypeExpression.toLowerCase().split( rspacesAjax ),
6671 				i = 0,
6672 				length = dataTypes.length,
6673 				dataType,
6674 				list,
6675 				placeBefore;
6676 
6677 			// For each dataType in the dataTypeExpression
6678 			for(; i < length; i++ ) {
6679 				dataType = dataTypes[ i ];
6680 				// We control if we're asked to add before
6681 				// any existing element
6682 				placeBefore = /^\+/.test( dataType );
6683 				if ( placeBefore ) {
6684 					dataType = dataType.substr( 1 ) || "*";
6685 				}
6686 				list = structure[ dataType ] = structure[ dataType ] || [];
6687 				// then we add to the structure accordingly
6688 				list[ placeBefore ? "unshift" : "push" ]( func );
6689 			}
6690 		}
6691 	};
6692 }
6693 
6694 // Base inspection function for prefilters and transports
6695 function inspectPrefiltersOrTransports( structure, options, originalOptions, jqXHR,
6696 		dataType /* internal */, inspected /* internal */ ) {
6697 
6698 	dataType = dataType || options.dataTypes[ 0 ];
6699 	inspected = inspected || {};
6700 
6701 	inspected[ dataType ] = true;
6702 
6703 	var list = structure[ dataType ],
6704 		i = 0,
6705 		length = list ? list.length : 0,
6706 		executeOnly = ( structure === prefilters ),
6707 		selection;
6708 
6709 	for(; i < length && ( executeOnly || !selection ); i++ ) {
6710 		selection = list[ i ]( options, originalOptions, jqXHR );
6711 		// If we got redirected to another dataType
6712 		// we try there if executing only and not done already
6713 		if ( typeof selection === "string" ) {
6714 			if ( !executeOnly || inspected[ selection ] ) {
6715 				selection = undefined;
6716 			} else {
6717 				options.dataTypes.unshift( selection );
6718 				selection = inspectPrefiltersOrTransports(
6719 						structure, options, originalOptions, jqXHR, selection, inspected );
6720 			}
6721 		}
6722 	}
6723 	// If we're only executing or nothing was selected
6724 	// we try the catchall dataType if not done already
6725 	if ( ( executeOnly || !selection ) && !inspected[ "*" ] ) {
6726 		selection = inspectPrefiltersOrTransports(
6727 				structure, options, originalOptions, jqXHR, "*", inspected );
6728 	}
6729 	// unnecessary when only executing (prefilters)
6730 	// but it'll be ignored by the caller in that case
6731 	return selection;
6732 }

6734 jQuery.fn.extend({
6735 	load: function( url, params, callback ) {
6736 		if ( typeof url !== "string" && _load ) {
6737 			return _load.apply( this, arguments );
6738 
6739 		// Don't do a request if no elements are being requested
6740 		} else if ( !this.length ) {
6741 			return this;
6742 		}
6743 
6744 		var off = url.indexOf( " " );
6745 		if ( off >= 0 ) {
6746 			var selector = url.slice( off, url.length );
6747 			url = url.slice( 0, off );
6748 		}
6749 
6750 		// Default to a GET request
6751 		var type = "GET";
6752 
6753 		// If the second parameter was provided
6754 		if ( params ) {
6755 			// If it's a function
6756 			if ( jQuery.isFunction( params ) ) {
6757 				// We assume that it's the callback
6758 				callback = params;
6759 				params = undefined;
6760 
6761 			// Otherwise, build a param string
6762 6763 			} else if ( typeof params === "object" ) {
6764 				params = jQuery.param( params, jQuery.ajaxSettings.traditional );
6765 				type = "POST";
6766 			}
6767 		}
6768 
6769 		var self = this;
6770 
6771 		// Request the remote document
6772 		jQuery.ajax({
6773 			url: url,
6774 			type: type,
6775 			dataType: "html",
6776 			data: params,
6777 			// Complete callback (responseText is used internally)
6778 			complete: function( jqXHR, status, responseText ) {
6779 				// Store the response as specified by the jqXHR object
6780 				responseText = jqXHR.responseText;
6781 				// If successful, inject the HTML into all the matched elements
6782 				if ( jqXHR.isResolved() ) {
6783 					// #4825: Get the actual response in case
6784 					// a dataFilter is present in ajaxSettings
6785 					jqXHR.done(function( r ) {
6786 						responseText = r;
6787 					});
6788 					// See if a selector was specified
6789 					self.html( selector ?
6790 						// Create a dummy div to hold the results
6791 						jQuery("<div>")
6792 							// inject the contents of the document in, removing the scripts
6793 							// to avoid any 'Permission Denied' errors in IE
6794 							.append(responseText.replace(rscript, ""))
6795 
6796 							// Locate the specified elements
6797 							.find(selector) :
6798 
6799 						// If not, just inject the full result
6800 						responseText );
6801 				}
6802 
6803 				if ( callback ) {
6804 					self.each( callback, [ responseText, status, jqXHR ] );
6805 				}
6806 			}
6807 		});
6808 
6809 		return this;
6810 	},

6829 				null :

6875 	// Creates a full fledged settings object into target
6876 	// with both ajaxSettings and settings fields.
6877 	// If target is omitted, writes into ajaxSettings.
6878 	ajaxSetup: function ( target, settings ) {
6879 		if ( !settings ) {
6880 			// Only one parameter, we extend ajaxSettings
6881 			settings = target;
6882 			target = jQuery.extend( true, jQuery.ajaxSettings, settings );
6883 		} else {
6884 			// target was provided, we extend into it
6885 			jQuery.extend( true, target, jQuery.ajaxSettings, settings );
6886 		}
6887 		// Flatten fields we don't want deep extended
6888 		for( var field in { context: 1, url: 1 } ) {
6889 			if ( field in settings ) {
6890 				target[ field ] = settings[ field ];
6891 			} else if( field in jQuery.ajaxSettings ) {
6892 				target[ field ] = jQuery.ajaxSettings[ field ];
6893 			}
6894 		}
6895 		return target;

6958 	// Main method
6959 	ajax: function( url, options ) {
6960 
6961 		// If url is an object, simulate pre-1.5 signature
6962 		if ( typeof url === "object" ) {
6963 			options = url;
6964 			url = undefined;
6965 		}
6966 
6967 		// Force options to be an object
6968 		options = options || {};
6969 
6970 		var // Create the final options object
6971 			s = jQuery.ajaxSetup( {}, options ),
6972 			// Callbacks context
6973 			callbackContext = s.context || s,
6974 			// Context for global events
6975 			// It's the callbackContext if one was provided in the options
6976 			// and if it's a DOM node or a jQuery collection
6977 			globalEventContext = callbackContext !== s &&
6978 				( callbackContext.nodeType || callbackContext instanceof jQuery ) ?
6979 						jQuery( callbackContext ) : jQuery.event,
6980 			// Deferreds
6981 			deferred = jQuery.Deferred(),
6982 			completeDeferred = jQuery._Deferred(),
6983 			// Status-dependent callbacks
6984 			statusCode = s.statusCode || {},
6985 			// ifModified key
6986 			ifModifiedKey,
6987 			// Headers (they are sent all at once)
6988 			requestHeaders = {},
6989 			requestHeadersNames = {},
6990 			// Response headers
6991 			responseHeadersString,
6992 			responseHeaders,
6993 			// transport
6994 			transport,
6995 			// timeout handle
6996 			timeoutTimer,
6997 			// Cross-domain detection vars
6998 			parts,
6999 			// The jqXHR state
7000 			state = 0,
7001 			// To know if global events are to be dispatched
7002 			fireGlobals,
7003 			// Loop variable
7004 			i,
7005 			// Fake xhr
7006 			jqXHR = {
7007 
7008 				readyState: 0,
7009 
7010 				// Caches the header
7011 				setRequestHeader: function( name, value ) {
7012 					if ( !state ) {
7013 						var lname = name.toLowerCase();
7014 						name = requestHeadersNames[ lname ] = requestHeadersNames[ lname ] || name;
7015 						requestHeaders[ name ] = value;
7016 					}
7017 					return this;
7018 				},
7019 
7020 				// Raw string
7021 				getAllResponseHeaders: function() {
7022 					return state === 2 ? responseHeadersString : null;
7023 				},
7024 
7025 				// Builds headers hashtable if needed
7026 				getResponseHeader: function( key ) {
7027 					var match;
7028 					if ( state === 2 ) {
7029 						if ( !responseHeaders ) {
7030 							responseHeaders = {};
7031 							while( ( match = rheaders.exec( responseHeadersString ) ) ) {
7032 								responseHeaders[ match[1].toLowerCase() ] = match[ 2 ];
7033 							}
7034 						}
7035 						match = responseHeaders[ key.toLowerCase() ];
7036 					}
7037 					return match === undefined ? null : match;
7038 				},
7039 
7040 				// Overrides response content-type header
7041 				overrideMimeType: function( type ) {
7042 					if ( !state ) {
7043 						s.mimeType = type;
7044 					}
7045 					return this;
7046 				},
7047 
7048 				// Cancel the request
7049 				abort: function( statusText ) {
7050 					statusText = statusText || "abort";
7051 					if ( transport ) {
7052 						transport.abort( statusText );
7053 					}
7054 					done( 0, statusText );
7055 					return this;
7056 				}
7057 			};
7058 
7059 		// Callback for when everything is done
7060 		// It is defined here because jslint complains if it is declared
7061 		// at the end of the function (which would be more logical and readable)
7062 		function done( status, statusText, responses, headers ) {
7063 
7064 			// Called once
7065 			if ( state === 2 ) {
7066 				return;
7067 			}
7068 
7069 			// State is "done" now
7070 			state = 2;
7071 
7072 			// Clear timeout if it exists
7073 			if ( timeoutTimer ) {
7074 				clearTimeout( timeoutTimer );
7075 			}
7076 
7077 			// Dereference transport for early garbage collection
7078 			// (no matter how long the jqXHR object will be used)
7079 			transport = undefined;
7080 
7081 			// Cache response headers
7082 			responseHeadersString = headers || "";
7083 
7084 			// Set readyState
7085 			jqXHR.readyState = status ? 4 : 0;
7086 
7087 			var isSuccess,
7088 				success,
7089 				error,
7090 				response = responses ? ajaxHandleResponses( s, jqXHR, responses ) : undefined,
7091 				lastModified,
7092 				etag;
7093 
7094 			// If successful, handle type chaining
7095 			if ( status >= 200 && status < 300 || status === 304 ) {
7096 
7097 				// Set the If-Modified-Since and/or If-None-Match header, if in ifModified mode.
7098 				if ( s.ifModified ) {
7099 
7100 					if ( ( lastModified = jqXHR.getResponseHeader( "Last-Modified" ) ) ) {
7101 						jQuery.lastModified[ ifModifiedKey ] = lastModified;
7102 					}
7103 					if ( ( etag = jqXHR.getResponseHeader( "Etag" ) ) ) {
7104 						jQuery.etag[ ifModifiedKey ] = etag;
7105 					}
7106 				}
7107 
7108 				// If not modified
7109 				if ( status === 304 ) {
7110 
7111 					statusText = "notmodified";
7112 					isSuccess = true;
7113 
7114 				// If we have data
7115 				} else {
7116 
7117 					try {
7118 						success = ajaxConvert( s, response );
7119 						statusText = "success";
7120 						isSuccess = true;
7121 					} catch(e) {
7122 						// We have a parsererror
7123 						statusText = "parsererror";
7124 						error = e;
7125 					}
7126 				}
7127 			} else {
7128 				// We extract error from statusText
7129 				// then normalize statusText and status for non-aborts
7130 				error = statusText;
7131 				if( !statusText || status ) {
7132 					statusText = "error";
7133 					if ( status < 0 ) {
7134 						status = 0;
7135 					}
7136 				}
7137 			}
7138 
7139 			// Set data for the fake xhr object
7140 			jqXHR.status = status;
7141 			jqXHR.statusText = statusText;
7142 
7143 			// Success/Error
7144 			if ( isSuccess ) {
7145 				deferred.resolveWith( callbackContext, [ success, statusText, jqXHR ] );
7146 			} else {
7147 				deferred.rejectWith( callbackContext, [ jqXHR, statusText, error ] );
7148 			}
7149 
7150 			// Status-dependent callbacks
7151 			jqXHR.statusCode( statusCode );
7152 			statusCode = undefined;
7153 
7154 			if ( fireGlobals ) {
7155 				globalEventContext.trigger( "ajax" + ( isSuccess ? "Success" : "Error" ),
7156 						[ jqXHR, s, isSuccess ? success : error ] );
7157 			}
7158 
7159 			// Complete
7160 			completeDeferred.resolveWith( callbackContext, [ jqXHR, statusText ] );
7161 
7162 			if ( fireGlobals ) {
7163 				globalEventContext.trigger( "ajaxComplete", [ jqXHR, s] );
7164 				// Handle the global AJAX counter
7165 				if ( !( --jQuery.active ) ) {
7166 					jQuery.event.trigger( "ajaxStop" );
7167 				}
7168 			}
7169 		}
7170 
7171 		// Attach deferreds
7172 		deferred.promise( jqXHR );
7173 		jqXHR.success = jqXHR.done;
7174 		jqXHR.error = jqXHR.fail;
7175 		jqXHR.complete = completeDeferred.done;
7176 
7177 		// Status-dependent callbacks
7178 		jqXHR.statusCode = function( map ) {
7179 			if ( map ) {
7180 				var tmp;
7181 				if ( state < 2 ) {
7182 					for( tmp in map ) {
7183 						statusCode[ tmp ] = [ statusCode[tmp], map[tmp] ];
7184 					}
7185 				} else {
7186 					tmp = map[ jqXHR.status ];
7187 					jqXHR.then( tmp, tmp );
7188 				}
7189 			}
7190 			return this;
7191 		};
7192 
7193 		// Remove hash character (#7531: and string promotion)
7194 		// Add protocol if not provided (#5866: IE7 issue with protocol-less urls)
7195 		// We also use the url parameter if available
7196 		s.url = ( ( url || s.url ) + "" ).replace( rhash, "" ).replace( rprotocol, ajaxLocParts[ 1 ] + "//" );
7197 
7198 		// Extract dataTypes list
7199 		s.dataTypes = jQuery.trim( s.dataType || "*" ).toLowerCase().split( rspacesAjax );
7200 
7201 		// Determine if a cross-domain request is in order
7202 		if ( s.crossDomain == null ) {
7203 			parts = rurl.exec( s.url.toLowerCase() );
7204 			s.crossDomain = !!( parts &&
7205 				( parts[ 1 ] != ajaxLocParts[ 1 ] || parts[ 2 ] != ajaxLocParts[ 2 ] ||
7206 					( parts[ 3 ] || ( parts[ 1 ] === "http:" ? 80 : 443 ) ) !=
7207 						( ajaxLocParts[ 3 ] || ( ajaxLocParts[ 1 ] === "http:" ? 80 : 443 ) ) )
7208 			);
7209 		}
7210 
7211 		// Convert data if not already a string
7212 		if ( s.data && s.processData && typeof s.data !== "string" ) {
7213 			s.data = jQuery.param( s.data, s.traditional );
7214 		}
7215 
7216 		// Apply prefilters
7217 		inspectPrefiltersOrTransports( prefilters, s, options, jqXHR );
7218 
7219 		// If request was aborted inside a prefiler, stop there
7220 		if ( state === 2 ) {
7221 			return false;
7222 		}
7223 
7224 		// We can fire global events as of now if asked to
7225 		fireGlobals = s.global;
7226 
7227 		// Uppercase the type
7228 		s.type = s.type.toUpperCase();
7229 
7230 		// Determine if request has content
7231 		s.hasContent = !rnoContent.test( s.type );
7232 
7233 		// Watch for a new set of requests
7234 		if ( fireGlobals && jQuery.active++ === 0 ) {
7235 			jQuery.event.trigger( "ajaxStart" );
7236 		}
7237 
7238 		// More options handling for requests with no content
7239 		if ( !s.hasContent ) {
7240 
7241 			// If data is available, append data to url
7242 			if ( s.data ) {
7243 				s.url += ( rquery.test( s.url ) ? "&" : "?" ) + s.data;
7244 			}
7245 
7246 			// Get ifModifiedKey before adding the anti-cache parameter
7247 			ifModifiedKey = s.url;
7248 
7249 			// Add anti-cache in url if needed
7250 			if ( s.cache === false ) {
7251 
7252 				var ts = jQuery.now(),
7253 					// try replacing _= if it is there
7254 					ret = s.url.replace( rts, "$1_=" + ts );
7255 
7256 				// if nothing was replaced, add timestamp to the end
7257 				s.url = ret + ( (ret === s.url ) ? ( rquery.test( s.url ) ? "&" : "?" ) + "_=" + ts : "" );
7258 			}
7259 		}
7260 
7261 		// Set the correct header, if data is being sent
7262 		if ( s.data && s.hasContent && s.contentType !== false || options.contentType ) {
7263 			jqXHR.setRequestHeader( "Content-Type", s.contentType );
7264 		}
7265 
7266 		// Set the If-Modified-Since and/or If-None-Match header, if in ifModified mode.
7267 		if ( s.ifModified ) {
7268 			ifModifiedKey = ifModifiedKey || s.url;
7269 			if ( jQuery.lastModified[ ifModifiedKey ] ) {
7270 				jqXHR.setRequestHeader( "If-Modified-Since", jQuery.lastModified[ ifModifiedKey ] );
7271 			}
7272 			if ( jQuery.etag[ ifModifiedKey ] ) {
7273 				jqXHR.setRequestHeader( "If-None-Match", jQuery.etag[ ifModifiedKey ] );
7274 			}
7275 		}
7276 
7277 		// Set the Accepts header for the server, depending on the dataType
7278 		jqXHR.setRequestHeader(
7279 			"Accept",
7280 			s.dataTypes[ 0 ] && s.accepts[ s.dataTypes[0] ] ?
7281 				s.accepts[ s.dataTypes[0] ] + ( s.dataTypes[ 0 ] !== "*" ? ", */*; q=0.01" : "" ) :
7282 				s.accepts[ "*" ]
7283 		);
7284 
7285 		// Check for headers option
7286 		for ( i in s.headers ) {
7287 			jqXHR.setRequestHeader( i, s.headers[ i ] );
7288 		}
7289 7290 
		// Allow custom headers/mimetypes and early abort
7291 		if ( s.beforeSend && ( s.beforeSend.call( callbackContext, jqXHR, s ) === false || state === 2 ) ) {
7292 				// Abort if not done already
7293 				jqXHR.abort();
7294 				return false;
7295 
7296 		}
7297 
7298 		// Install callbacks on deferreds
7299 		for ( i in { success: 1, error: 1, complete: 1 } ) {
7300 			jqXHR[ i ]( s[ i ] );
7301 		}
7302 
7303 		// Get transport
7304 		transport = inspectPrefiltersOrTransports( transports, s, options, jqXHR );
7305 
7306 		// If no transport, we auto-abort
7307 		if ( !transport ) {
7308 			done( -1, "No Transport" );
7309 		} else {
7310 			jqXHR.readyState = 1;
7311 			// Send global event
7312 			if ( fireGlobals ) {
7313 				globalEventContext.trigger( "ajaxSend", [ jqXHR, s ] );
7314 			}
7315 			// Timeout
7316 			if ( s.async && s.timeout > 0 ) {
7317 				timeoutTimer = setTimeout( function(){
7318 					jqXHR.abort( "timeout" );
7319 				}, s.timeout );
7320 			}
7321 
7322 			try {
7323 				state = 1;
7324 				transport.send( requestHeaders, done );
7325 			} catch (e) {
7326 				// Propagate exception as error if not done
7327 				if ( status < 2 ) {
7328 					done( -1, e );
7329 				// Simply rethrow otherwise
7330 				} else {
7331 					jQuery.error( e );
7332 				}
7333 			}
7334 		}
7335 
7336 		return jqXHR;
7337 	},
7338 
7339 	// Serialize an array of form elements or a set of
7340 	// key/values into a query string
7341 	param: function( a, traditional ) {
7342 		var s = [],
7343 			add = function( key, value ) {
7344 				// If value is a function, invoke it and return its value
7345 7346 				value = jQuery.isFunction( value ) ? value() : value;
7347 				s[ s.length ] = encodeURIComponent( key ) + "=" + encodeURIComponent( value );
7348 			};
7349 
7350 		// Set traditional to true for jQuery <= 1.3.2 behavior.
7351 		if ( traditional === undefined ) {
7352 			traditional = jQuery.ajaxSettings.traditional;
7353 		}
7354 
7355 		// If an array was passed in, assume that it is an array of form elements.
7356 		if ( jQuery.isArray( a ) || ( a.jquery && !jQuery.isPlainObject( a ) ) ) {
7357 			// Serialize the form elements
7358 			jQuery.each( a, function() {
7359 				add( this.name, this.value );
7360 			});
7361 
7362 		} else {
7363 			// If traditional, encode the "old" way (the way 1.3.2 or older
7364 			// did it), otherwise encode params recursively.
7365 			for ( var prefix in a ) {
7366 				buildParams( prefix, a[ prefix ], traditional, add );
7367 			}
7368 		}
7369 
7370 		// Return the resulting serialization
7371 		return s.join( "&" ).replace( r20, "+" );
7372 	}
7373 });
7374 
7375 function buildParams( prefix, obj, traditional, add ) {
7376 	if ( jQuery.isArray( obj ) ) {
7377 		// Serialize array item.
7378 		jQuery.each( obj, function( i, v ) {
7379 			if ( traditional || rbracket.test( prefix ) ) {
7380 				// Treat each array item as a scalar.
7381 				add( prefix, v );
7382 
7383 			} else {
7384 				// If array item is non-scalar (array or object), encode its
7385 				// numeric index to resolve deserialization ambiguity issues.
7386 				// Note that rack (as of 1.0.0) can't currently deserialize
7387 				// nested arrays properly, and attempting to do so may cause
7388 				// a server error. Possible fixes are to modify rack's
7389 				// deserialization algorithm or to provide an option or flag
7390 				// to force array serialization to be shallow.
7391 				buildParams( prefix + "[" + ( typeof v === "object" || jQuery.isArray(v) ? i : "" ) + "]", v, traditional, add );
7392 			}
7393 		});
7394 
7395 	} else if ( !traditional && obj != null && typeof obj === "object" ) {
7396 		// Serialize object item.
7397 		for ( var name in obj ) {
7398 			buildParams( prefix + "[" + name + "]", obj[ name ], traditional, add );
7399 		}
7400 
7401 	} else {
7402 		// Serialize scalar item.
7403 		add( prefix, obj );
7404 	}
7405 }

7408 // Want to move this to jQuery.ajax some day
7409 jQuery.extend({
7410 
7411 	// Counter for holding the number of active queries
7412 	active: 0,
7413 
7414 	// Last-Modified header cache for next request
7415 	lastModified: {},
7416 	etag: {}
7417

7420 /* Handles responses to an ajax request:
7421  * - sets all responseXXX fields accordingly
7422  * - finds the right dataType (mediates between content-type and expected dataType)
7423  * - returns the corresponding response
7424  */
7425 function ajaxHandleResponses( s, jqXHR, responses ) {
7426 
7427 	var contents = s.contents,
7428 		dataTypes = s.dataTypes,
7429 		responseFields = s.responseFields,
7430 		ct,
7431 		type,
7432 		finalDataType,
7433 		firstDataType;
7434 
7435 	// Fill responseXXX fields
7436 	for( type in responseFields ) {
7437 		if ( type in responses ) {
7438 			jqXHR[ responseFields[type] ] = responses[ type ];
7439 		}
7440 	}
7441 
7442 	// Remove auto dataType and get content-type in the process
7443 	while( dataTypes[ 0 ] === "*" ) {
7444 		dataTypes.shift();
7445 		if ( ct === undefined ) {
7446 			ct = s.mimeType || jqXHR.getResponseHeader( "content-type" );
7447 		}
7448 	}
7449 
7450 	// Check if we're dealing with a known content-type
7451 	if ( ct ) {
7452 		for ( type in contents ) {
7453 			if ( contents[ type ] && contents[ type ].test( ct ) ) {
7454 				dataTypes.unshift( type );
7455 				break;
7456 			}
7457 		}
7458 	}
7459 
7460 	// Check to see if we have a response for the expected dataType
7461 	if ( dataTypes[ 0 ] in responses ) {
7462 		finalDataType = dataTypes[ 0 ];
7463 	} else {
7464 		// Try convertible dataTypes
7465 		for ( type in responses ) {
7466 			if ( !dataTypes[ 0 ] || s.converters[ type + " " + dataTypes[0] ] ) {
7467 				finalDataType = type;
7468 				break;
7469 			}
7470 			if ( !firstDataType ) {
7471 				firstDataType = type;
7472 			}
7473 		}
7474 		// Or just use first one
7475 		finalDataType = finalDataType || firstDataType;
7476 	}
7477 
7478 	// If we found a dataType
7479 	// We add the dataType to the list if needed
7480 	// and return the corresponding response
7481 	if ( finalDataType ) {
7482 		if ( finalDataType !== dataTypes[ 0 ] ) {
7483 			dataTypes.unshift( finalDataType );
7484 		}
7485 		return responses[ finalDataType ];
7486 	}
7487 }
7488 
7489 // Chain conversions given the request and the original response
7490 function ajaxConvert( s, response ) {
7491 
7492 	// Apply the dataFilter if provided
7493 	if ( s.dataFilter ) {
7494 		response = s.dataFilter( response, s.dataType );
7495 	}
7496 
7497 	var dataTypes = s.dataTypes,
7498 		converters = {},
7499 		i,
7500 		key,
7501 		length = dataTypes.length,
7502 		tmp,
7503 		// Current and previous dataTypes
7504 		current = dataTypes[ 0 ],
7505 		prev,
7506 		// Conversion expression
7507 		conversion,
7508 		// Conversion function
7509 		conv,
7510 		// Conversion functions (transitive conversion)
7511 		conv1,
7512 		conv2;
7513 
7514 	// For each dataType in the chain
7515 	for( i = 1; i < length; i++ ) {
7516 
7517 		// Create converters map
7518 		// with lowercased keys
7519 		if ( i === 1 ) {
7520 			for( key in s.converters ) {
7521 				if( typeof key === "string" ) {
7522 					converters[ key.toLowerCase() ] = s.converters[ key ];
7523 				}
7524 			}
7525 		}
7526 
7527 		// Get the dataTypes
7528 		prev = current;
7529 		current = dataTypes[ i ];
7530 
7531 		// If current is auto dataType, update it to prev
7532 		if( current === "*" ) {
7533 			current = prev;
7534 		// If no auto and dataTypes are actually different
7535 		} else if ( prev !== "*" && prev !== current ) {
7536 
7537 			// Get the converter
7538 			conversion = prev + " " + current;
7539 			conv = converters[ conversion ] || converters[ "* " + current ];
7540 
7541 			// If there is no direct converter, search transitively
7542 			if ( !conv ) {
7543 				conv2 = undefined;
7544 				for( conv1 in converters ) {
7545 					tmp = conv1.split( " " );
7546 					if ( tmp[ 0 ] === prev || tmp[ 0 ] === "*" ) {
7547 						conv2 = converters[ tmp[1] + " " + current ];
7548 						if ( conv2 ) {
7549 							conv1 = converters[ conv1 ];
7550 							if ( conv1 === true ) {
7551 								conv = conv2;
7552 							} else if ( conv2 === true ) {
7553 								conv = conv1;
7554 							}
7555 							break;
7556 						}
7557 					}
7558 				}
7559 			}
7560 			// If we found no converter, dispatch an error
7561 			if ( !( conv || conv2 ) ) {
7562 				jQuery.error( "No conversion from " + conversion.replace(" "," to ") );
7563 			}
7564 			// If found converter is not an equivalence
7565 			if ( conv !== true ) {
7566 				// Convert with 1 or 2 converters accordingly
7567 				response = conv ? conv( response ) : conv2( conv1(response) );
7568 			}
7569 		}
7570 	}
7571 	return response;
7572 }

7577 var jsc = jQuery.now(),
7578 	jsre = /(\=)\?(&|$)|\?\?/i;
7579 
7580 // Default jsonp settings
7581 jQuery.ajaxSetup({

7583 	jsonpCallback: function() {
7584 		return jQuery.expando + "_" + ( jsc++ );
7585 	}

7588 // Detect, normalize options and install callbacks for jsonp requests
7589 jQuery.ajaxPrefilter( "json jsonp", function( s, originalSettings, jqXHR ) {
7590 
7591 	var inspectData = s.contentType === "application/x-www-form-urlencoded" &&
7592 		( typeof s.data === "string" );
7593 
7594 	if ( s.dataTypes[ 0 ] === "jsonp" ||
7595 		s.jsonp !== false && ( jsre.test( s.url ) ||
7596 				inspectData && jsre.test( s.data ) ) ) {
7597 
7598 		var responseContainer,
7599 			jsonpCallback = s.jsonpCallback =
7600 				jQuery.isFunction( s.jsonpCallback ) ? s.jsonpCallback() : s.jsonpCallback,
7601 			previous = window[ jsonpCallback ],
7602 			url = s.url,
7603 			data = s.data,
7604 			replace = "$1" + jsonpCallback + "$2";
7605 
7606 		if ( s.jsonp !== false ) {
7607 			url = url.replace( jsre, replace );
7608 			if ( s.url === url ) {
7609 				if ( inspectData ) {
7610 					data = data.replace( jsre, replace );
7611 				}
7612 				if ( s.data === data ) {
7613 					// Add callback manually
7614 					url += (/\?/.test( url ) ? "&" : "?") + s.jsonp + "=" + jsonpCallback;
7615 				}
7616 			}
7617 		}
7618 
7619 		s.url = url;
7620 		s.data = data;
7621 
7622 		// Install callback
7623 		window[ jsonpCallback ] = function( response ) {
7624 			responseContainer = [ response ];
7625 		};
7626 
7627 		// Clean-up function
7628 		jqXHR.always(function() {
7629 			// Set callback back to previous value
7630 			window[ jsonpCallback ] = previous;
7631 			// Call if it was a function and we have a response
7632 			if ( responseContainer && jQuery.isFunction( previous ) ) {
7633 				window[ jsonpCallback ]( responseContainer[ 0 ] );
7634 			}
7635 		});
7636 
7637 		// Use data converter to retrieve json after script execution
7638 		s.converters["script json"] = function() {
7639 			if ( !responseContainer ) {
7640 				jQuery.error( jsonpCallback + " was not called" );
7641 			}
7642 			return responseContainer[ 0 ];
7643 		};
7644 
7645 		// force json dataType
7646 		s.dataTypes[ 0 ] = "json";
7647 
7648 		// Delegate to script
7649 		return "script";
7650 	}
7651 });

7683 // Bind script tag hack transport
7684 jQuery.ajaxTransport( "script", function(s) {
7685 
7686 	// This transport only deals with cross domain requests
7687 	if ( s.crossDomain ) {
7688 
7689 		var script,
7690 			head = document.head || document.getElementsByTagName( "head" )[0] || document.documentElement;
7691 
7692 		return {
7693 
7694 			send: function( _, callback ) {
7695 
7696 				script = document.createElement( "script" );
7697 
7698 				script.async = "async";
7699 
7700 				if ( s.scriptCharset ) {
7701 					script.charset = s.scriptCharset;
7702 				}
7703 
7704 				script.src = s.url;
7705 
7706 				// Attach handlers for all browsers
7707 				script.onload = script.onreadystatechange = function( _, isAbort ) {
7708 
7709 					if ( isAbort || !script.readyState || /loaded|complete/.test( script.readyState ) ) {
7710 
7711 						// Handle memory leak in IE
7712 						script.onload = script.onreadystatechange = null;
7713 
7714 						// Remove the script
7715 						if ( head && script.parentNode ) {
7716 							head.removeChild( script );
7717 						}
7718 
7719 						// Dereference the script
7720 						script = undefined;
7721 
7722 						// Callback if not abort
7723 						if ( !isAbort ) {
7724 							callback( 200, "success" );
7725 						}
7726 					}
7727 				};
7728 				// Use insertBefore instead of appendChild  to circumvent an IE6 bug.
7729 				// This arises when a base node is used (#2709 and #4378).
7730 				head.insertBefore( script, head.firstChild );
7731 			},
7732 
7733 			abort: function() {
7734 				if ( script ) {
7735 					script.onload( 0, 1 );
7736 				}
7737 			}
7738 		};
7739 	}
7740 });

7755 // Functions to create xhrs
7756 function createStandardXHR() {
7757 	try {
7758 		return new window.XMLHttpRequest();
7759 	} catch( e ) {}

7761 
7762 function createActiveXHR() {
7763 	try {
7764 		return new window.ActiveXObject( "Microsoft.XMLHTTP" );
7765 	} catch( e ) {}
7766 }
7767 
7768 // Create the request object
7769 // (This is still attached to ajaxSettings for backward compatibility)
7770 jQuery.ajaxSettings.xhr = window.ActiveXObject ?
7771 	/* Microsoft failed to properly
7772 	 * implement the XMLHttpRequest in IE7 (can't request local files),
7773 	 * so we use the ActiveXObject when it is available
7774 	 * Additionally XMLHttpRequest can be disabled in IE7/IE8 so
7775 	 * we need a fallback.
7776 	 */
7777 	function() {
7778 		return !this.isLocal && createStandardXHR() || createActiveXHR();
7779 	} :
7780 	// For all other browsers, use the standard XMLHttpRequest object
7781 	createStandardXHR;

7783 // Determine support properties
7784 (function( xhr ) {
7785 	jQuery.extend( jQuery.support, {
7786 		ajax: !!xhr,
7787 		cors: !!xhr && ( "withCredentials" in xhr )
7788 	});
7789 })( jQuery.ajaxSettings.xhr() );

7791 // Create transport if the browser can provide an xhr
7792 if ( jQuery.support.ajax ) {
7793 
7794 	jQuery.ajaxTransport(function( s ) {
7795 		// Cross domain only allowed if supported through XMLHttpRequest
7796 		if ( !s.crossDomain || jQuery.support.cors ) {
7797 
7798 			var callback;
7799 
7800 			return {
7801 				send: function( headers, complete ) {
7802 
7803 					// Get a new xhr
7804 					var xhr = s.xhr(),
7805 						handle,
7806 						i;
7807 
7808 					// Open the socket
7809 					// Passing null username, generates a login popup on Opera (#2865)
7810 					if ( s.username ) {
7811 						xhr.open( s.type, s.url, s.async, s.username, s.password );
7812 					} else {
7813 						xhr.open( s.type, s.url, s.async );
7814 					}
7815 
7816 					// Apply custom fields if provided
7817 					if ( s.xhrFields ) {
7818 						for ( i in s.xhrFields ) {
7819 							xhr[ i ] = s.xhrFields[ i ];
7820 						}
7821 					}
7822 
7823 					// Override mime type if needed
7824 					if ( s.mimeType && xhr.overrideMimeType ) {
7825 						xhr.overrideMimeType( s.mimeType );
7826 					}
7827 
7828 					// X-Requested-With header
7829 					// For cross-domain requests, seeing as conditions for a preflight are
7830 					// akin to a jigsaw puzzle, we simply never set it to be sure.
7831 					// (it can always be set on a per-request basis or even using ajaxSetup)
7832 					// For same-domain requests, won't change header if already provided.
7833 					if ( !s.crossDomain && !headers["X-Requested-With"] ) {
7834 						headers[ "X-Requested-With" ] = "XMLHttpRequest";
7835 					}
7836 
7837 					// Need an extra try/catch for cross domain requests in Firefox 3
7838 					try {
7839 						for ( i in headers ) {
7840 							xhr.setRequestHeader( i, headers[ i ] );
7841 						}
7842 					} catch( _ ) {}
7843 
7844 					// Do send the request
7845 					// This may raise an exception which is actually
7846 					// handled in jQuery.ajax (so no try/catch here)
7847 					xhr.send( ( s.hasContent && s.data ) || null );
7848 
7849 					// Listener
7850 					callback = function( _, isAbort ) {
7851 
7852 						var status,
7853 							statusText,
7854 							responseHeaders,
7855 							responses,
7856 							xml;
7857 
7858 						// Firefox throws exceptions when accessing properties
7859 						// of an xhr when a network error occured
7860 						// http://helpful.knobs-dials.com/index.php/Component_returned_failure_code:_0x80040111_(NS_ERROR_NOT_AVAILABLE)
7861 						try {
7862 
7863 							// Was never called and is aborted or complete
7864 							if ( callback && ( isAbort || xhr.readyState === 4 ) ) {
7865 
7866 								// Only called once
7867 								callback = undefined;
7868 
7869 								// Do not keep as active anymore
7870 								if ( handle ) {
7871 									xhr.onreadystatechange = jQuery.noop;
7872 									if ( xhrOnUnloadAbort ) {
7873 										delete xhrCallbacks[ handle ];
7874 									}
7875 								}
7876 
7877 								// If it's an abort
7878 								if ( isAbort ) {
7879 									// Abort it manually if needed
7880 									if ( xhr.readyState !== 4 ) {
7881 										xhr.abort();
7882 									}
7883 								} else {
7884 									status = xhr.status;
7885 									responseHeaders = xhr.getAllResponseHeaders();
7886 									responses = {};
7887 									xml = xhr.responseXML;
7888 
7889 									// Construct response list
7890 									if ( xml && xml.documentElement /* #4958 */ ) {
7891 										responses.xml = xml;
7892 									}
7893 									responses.text = xhr.responseText;
7894 
7895 									// Firefox throws an exception when accessing
7896 									// statusText for faulty cross-domain requests
7897 									try {
7898 										statusText = xhr.statusText;
7899 									} catch( e ) {
7900 										// We normalize with Webkit giving an empty statusText
7901 										statusText = "";
7902 									}
7903 
7904 									// Filter status for non standard behaviors
7905 
7906 									// If the request is local and we have data: assume a success
7907 									// (success with no data won't get notified, that's the best we
7908 									// can do given current implementations)
7909 									if ( !status && s.isLocal && !s.crossDomain ) {
7910 										status = responses.text ? 200 : 404;
7911 									// IE - #1450: sometimes returns 1223 when it should be 204
7912 									} else if ( status === 1223 ) {
7913 										status = 204;
7914 									}
7915 								}
7916 							}
7917 						} catch( firefoxAccessException ) {
7918 							if ( !isAbort ) {
7919 								complete( -1, firefoxAccessException );
7920 							}
7921 						}
7922 
7923 						// Call complete if needed
7924 						if ( responses ) {
7925 							complete( status, statusText, responses, responseHeaders );
7926 						}
7927 					};
7928 
7929 					// if we're in sync mode or it's in cache
7930 					// and has been retrieved directly (IE6 & IE7)
7931 					// we need to manually fire the callback
7932 					if ( !s.async || xhr.readyState === 4 ) {
7933 						callback();
7934 					} else {
7935 						handle = ++xhrId;
7936 						if ( xhrOnUnloadAbort ) {
7937 							// Create the active xhrs callbacks list if needed
7938 							// and attach the unload handler
7939 							if ( !xhrCallbacks ) {
7940 								xhrCallbacks = {};
7941 								jQuery( window ).unload( xhrOnUnloadAbort );
7942 							}
7943 							// Add to list of active xhrs callbacks
7944 							xhrCallbacks[ handle ] = callback;
7945 						}
7946 						xhr.onreadystatechange = callback;
7947 					}
7948 				},
7949 
7950 				abort: function() {
7951 					if ( callback ) {
7952 						callback(0,1);
7953 					}
7954 				}
7955 			};
7956 		}
7957 	});
7958 }

7963 var elemdisplay = {},

7969 		// height animations
7970 		[ "height", "marginTop", "marginBottom", "paddingTop", "paddingBottom" ],
7971 		// width animations
