7981 jQuery.fn.extend({
7982 	show: function( speed, easing, callback ) {
7983 		var elem, display;
7984 
7985 		if ( speed || speed === 0 ) {
7986 			return this.animate( genFx("show", 3), speed, easing, callback);
7987 
7988 		} else {
7989 			for ( var i = 0, j = this.length; i < j; i++ ) {
7990 				elem = this[i];
7991 
7992 				if ( elem.style ) {
7993 					display = elem.style.display;
7994 
7995 					// Reset the inline display of this element to learn if it is
7996 					// being hidden by cascaded rules or not
7997 					if ( !jQuery._data(elem, "olddisplay") && display === "none" ) {
7998 						display = elem.style.display = "";
7999 					}
8000 
8001 					// Set elements which have been overridden with display: none
8002 					// in a stylesheet to whatever the default browser style is
8003 					// for such an element
8004 					if ( display === "" && jQuery.css( elem, "display" ) === "none" ) {
8005 						jQuery._data(elem, "olddisplay", defaultDisplay(elem.nodeName));
8006 					}
8007 				}
8008 			}
8009 
8010 			// Set the display of most of the elements in a second loop
8011 			// to avoid the constant reflow
8012 			for ( i = 0; i < j; i++ ) {
8013 				elem = this[i];
8014 
8015 				if ( elem.style ) {
8016 					display = elem.style.display;
8017 
8018 					if ( display === "" || display === "none" ) {
8019 						elem.style.display = jQuery._data(elem, "olddisplay") || "";
8020 					}
8021 				}
8022 			}
8023 
8024 			return this;
8025 		}
8026 	},
8027 
8028 	hide: function( speed, easing, callback ) {
8029 		if ( speed || speed === 0 ) {
8030 			return this.animate( genFx("hide", 3), speed, easing, callback);
8031 
8032 		} else {
8033 			for ( var i = 0, j = this.length; i < j; i++ ) {
8034 				if ( this[i].style ) {
8035 					var display = jQuery.css( this[i], "display" );
8036 
8037 					if ( display !== "none" && !jQuery._data( this[i], "olddisplay" ) ) {
8038 						jQuery._data( this[i], "olddisplay", display );
8039 					}
8040 				}
8041 			}
8042 
8043 			// Set the display of the elements in a second loop
8044 			// to avoid the constant reflow
8045 			for ( i = 0; i < j; i++ ) {
8046 				if ( this[i].style ) {
8047 					this[i].style.display = "none";
8048 				}
8049 			}
8050 
8051 			return this;
8052 		}
8053 	},
8054 
8055 	// Save the old toggle function
8056 	_toggle: jQuery.fn.toggle,
8057 
8058 	toggle: function( fn, fn2, callback ) {
8059 		var bool = typeof fn === "boolean";
8060 
8061 		if ( jQuery.isFunction(fn) && jQuery.isFunction(fn2) ) {
8062 			this._toggle.apply( this, arguments );
8063 
8064 		} else if ( fn == null || bool ) {
8065 			this.each(function() {
8066 				var state = bool ? fn : jQuery(this).is(":hidden");
8067 				jQuery(this)[ state ? "show" : "hide" ]();
8068 			});
8069 
8070 		} else {
8071 			this.animate(genFx("toggle", 3), fn, fn2, callback);
8072 		}
8073 
8074 		return this;
8075 	},
8076 
8077 	fadeTo: function( speed, to, easing, callback ) {
8078 		return this.filter(":hidden").css("opacity", 0).show().end()
8079 					.animate({opacity: to}, speed, easing, callback);
8080 	},
8081 
8082 	animate: function( prop, speed, easing, callback ) {
8083 		var optall = jQuery.speed(speed, easing, callback);
8084 
8085 		if ( jQuery.isEmptyObject( prop ) ) {
8086 			return this.each( optall.complete, [ false ] );
8087 		}
8088 
8089 		// Do not change referenced properties as per-property easing will be lost
8090 		prop = jQuery.extend( {}, prop );
8091 
8092 		return this[ optall.queue === false ? "each" : "queue" ](function() {
8093 			// XXX 'this' does not always have a nodeName when running the
8094 			// test suite
8095 
8096 			if ( optall.queue === false ) {
8097 				jQuery._mark( this );
8098 			}
8099 
8100 			var opt = jQuery.extend( {}, optall ),
8101 				isElement = this.nodeType === 1,
8102 				hidden = isElement && jQuery(this).is(":hidden"),
8103 				name, val, p,
8104 				display, e,
8105 				parts, start, end, unit;
8106 
8107 			// will store per property easing and be used to determine when an animation is complete
8108 			opt.animatedProperties = {};
8109 
8110 			for ( p in prop ) {
8111 
8112 				// property name normalization
8113 				name = jQuery.camelCase( p );
8114 				if ( p !== name ) {
8115 					prop[ name ] = prop[ p ];
8116 					delete prop[ p ];
8117 				}
8118 
8119 				val = prop[ name ];
8120 
8121 				// easing resolution: per property > opt.specialEasing > opt.easing > 'swing' (default)
8122 				if ( jQuery.isArray( val ) ) {
8123 					opt.animatedProperties[ name ] = val[ 1 ];
8124 					val = prop[ name ] = val[ 0 ];
8125 				} else {
8126 					opt.animatedProperties[ name ] = opt.specialEasing && opt.specialEasing[ name ] || opt.easing || 'swing';
8127 				}
8128 
8129 				if ( val === "hide" && hidden || val === "show" && !hidden ) {
8130 					return opt.complete.call( this );
8131 				}
8132 
8133 				if ( isElement && ( name === "height" || name === "width" ) ) {
8134 					// Make sure that nothing sneaks out
8135 					// Record all 3 overflow attributes because IE does not
8136 					// change the overflow attribute when overflowX and
8137 					// overflowY are set to the same value
8138 					opt.overflow = [ this.style.overflow, this.style.overflowX, this.style.overflowY ];
8139 
8140 					// Set display property to inline-block for height/width
8141 					// animations on inline elements that are having width/height
8142 					// animated
8143 					if ( jQuery.css( this, "display" ) === "inline" &&
8144 							jQuery.css( this, "float" ) === "none" ) {
8145 						if ( !jQuery.support.inlineBlockNeedsLayout ) {
8146 							this.style.display = "inline-block";
8147 
8148 						} else {
8149 							display = defaultDisplay( this.nodeName );
8150 
8151 							// inline-level elements accept inline-block;
8152 							// block-level elements need to be inline with layout
8153 							if ( display === "inline" ) {
8154 								this.style.display = "inline-block";
8155 
8156 							} else {
8157 								this.style.display = "inline";
8158 								this.style.zoom = 1;
8159 							}
8160 						}
8161 					}
8162 				}
8163 			}
8164 
8165 			if ( opt.overflow != null ) {
8166 				this.style.overflow = "hidden";
8167 			}
8168 
8169 			for ( p in prop ) {
8170 				e = new jQuery.fx( this, opt, p );
8171 				val = prop[ p ];
8172 
8173 				if ( rfxtypes.test(val) ) {
8174 					e[ val === "toggle" ? hidden ? "show" : "hide" : val ]();
8175 
8176 				} else {
8177 					parts = rfxnum.exec( val );
8178 					start = e.cur();
8179 
8180 					if ( parts ) {
8181 						end = parseFloat( parts[2] );
8182 						unit = parts[3] || ( jQuery.cssNumber[ p ] ? "" : "px" );
8183 
8184 						// We need to compute starting value
8185 						if ( unit !== "px" ) {
8186 							jQuery.style( this, p, (end || 1) + unit);
8187 							start = ((end || 1) / e.cur()) * start;
8188 							jQuery.style( this, p, start + unit);
8189 						}
8190 
8191 						// If a +=/-= token was provided, we're doing a relative animation
8192 						if ( parts[1] ) {
8193 							end = ( (parts[ 1 ] === "-=" ? -1 : 1) * end ) + start;
8194 						}
8195 
8196 						e.custom( start, end, unit );
8197 
8198 					} else {
8199 8200 						e.custom( start, val, "" );
8201 					}
8202 				}
8203 			}
8204 
8205 			// For JS strict compliance
8206 			return true;
8207 		});
8208 	},
8209 
8210 	stop: function( clearQueue, gotoEnd ) {
8211 		if ( clearQueue ) {
8212 			this.queue([]);
8213 		}
8214 
8215 		this.each(function() {
8216 			var timers = jQuery.timers,
8217 				i = timers.length;
8218 			// clear marker counters if we know they won't be
8219 			if ( !gotoEnd ) {
8220 				jQuery._unmark( true, this );
8221 			}
8222 			while ( i-- ) {
8223 				if ( timers[i].elem === this ) {
8224 					if (gotoEnd) {
8225 						// force the next step to be the last
8226 						timers[i](true);
8227 					}
8228 
8229 					timers.splice(i, 1);
8230 				}
8231 			}
8232 		});
8233 
8234 		// start the next in the queue if the last step wasn't forced
8235 		if ( !gotoEnd ) {
8236 			this.dequeue();
8237 		}
8238 
8239 		return this;
8240 	}
8241 
8242 });

8244 // Animations created synchronously will run synchronously
8245 function createFxNow() {
8246 	setTimeout( clearFxNow, 0 );
8247 	return ( fxNow = jQuery.now() );
8248 }
8249 
8250 function clearFxNow() {
8251 	fxNow = undefined;
8252 }
8253 
8254 // Generate parameters to create a standard animation
8255 function genFx( type, num ) {
8256 	var obj = {};
8257 
8258 	jQuery.each( fxAttrs.concat.apply([], fxAttrs.slice(0,num)), function() {
8259 		obj[ this ] = type;
8260 	});
8261 
8262 	return obj;
8263 }

8265 // Generate shortcuts for custom animations
8266 jQuery.each({
8267 	slideDown: genFx("show", 1),
8268 	slideUp: genFx("hide", 1),
8269 	slideToggle: genFx("toggle", 1),
8270 	fadeIn: { opacity: "show" },
8271 	fadeOut: { opacity: "hide" },
8272 	fadeToggle: { opacity: "toggle" }
8273 }, function( name, props ) {
8274 	jQuery.fn[ name ] = function( speed, easing, callback ) {
8275 		return this.animate( props, speed, easing, callback );
8276 	};
8277 });
8278 
8279 jQuery.extend({
8280 	speed: function( speed, easing, fn ) {
8281 		var opt = speed && typeof speed === "object" ? jQuery.extend({}, speed) : {
8282 			complete: fn || !fn && easing ||
8283 				jQuery.isFunction( speed ) && speed,
8284 			duration: speed,
8285 			easing: fn && easing || easing && !jQuery.isFunction(easing) && easing
8286 		};
8287 
8288 		opt.duration = jQuery.fx.off ? 0 : typeof opt.duration === "number" ? opt.duration :
8289 			opt.duration in jQuery.fx.speeds ? jQuery.fx.speeds[opt.duration] : jQuery.fx.speeds._default;
8290 
8291 		// Queueing
8292 		opt.old = opt.complete;
8293 		opt.complete = function( noUnmark ) {
8294 			if ( opt.queue !== false ) {
8295 				jQuery.dequeue( this );
8296 			} else if ( noUnmark !== false ) {
8297 				jQuery._unmark( this );
8298 			}
8299 
8300 			if ( jQuery.isFunction( opt.old ) ) {
8301 				opt.old.call( this );
8302 8303 			}
8304 		};
8305 
8306 		return opt;
8307 	},
8308 
8309 	easing: {
8310 		linear: function( p, n, firstNum, diff ) {
8311 			return firstNum + diff * p;
8312 		},
8313 		swing: function( p, n, firstNum, diff ) {
8314 			return ((-Math.cos(p*Math.PI)/2) + 0.5) * diff + firstNum;
8315 		}
8316 	},

8319

8321 		this.options = options;
8322 		this.elem = elem;
8323 		this.prop = prop;
8324 
8325 		options.orig = options.orig || {};
8326 	}

8330 jQuery.fx.prototype = {
8331 	// Simple function for setting a style value
8332 	update: function() {
8333 		if ( this.options.step ) {
8334 			this.options.step.call( this.elem, this.now, this );
8335 		}
8336 
8337 		(jQuery.fx.step[this.prop] || jQuery.fx.step._default)( this );
8338 	},
8339 
8340 	// Get the current size
8341 	cur: function() {
8342 		if ( this.elem[this.prop] != null && (!this.elem.style || this.elem.style[this.prop] == null) ) {
8343 			return this.elem[ this.prop ];
8344 		}
8345 
8346 		var parsed,
8347 			r = jQuery.css( this.elem, this.prop );
8348 		// Empty strings, null, undefined and "auto" are converted to 0,
8349 		// complex values such as "rotate(1rad)" are returned as is,
8350 		// simple values such as "10px" are parsed to Float.
8351 		return isNaN( parsed = parseFloat( r ) ) ? !r || r === "auto" ? 0 : r : parsed;
8352 	},
8353 
8354 	// Start an animation from one number to another
8355 	custom: function( from, to, unit ) {
8356 		var self = this,
8357 			fx = jQuery.fx,
8358 			raf;
8359 
8360 		this.startTime = fxNow || createFxNow();
8361 		this.start = from;
8362 		this.end = to;
8363 		this.unit = unit || this.unit || ( jQuery.cssNumber[ this.prop ] ? "" : "px" );
8364 		this.now = this.start;
8365 		this.pos = this.state = 0;
8366 
8367 		function t( gotoEnd ) {
8368 			return self.step(gotoEnd);
8369 		}
8370 
8371 		t.elem = this.elem;
8372 
8373 		if ( t() && jQuery.timers.push(t) && !timerId ) {
8374 			// Use requestAnimationFrame instead of setInterval if available
8375 			if ( requestAnimationFrame ) {
8376 				timerId = 1;
8377 				raf = function() {
8378 					// When timerId gets set to null at any point, this stops
8379 					if ( timerId ) {
8380 						requestAnimationFrame( raf );
8381 						fx.tick();
8382 					}
8383 				};
8384 				requestAnimationFrame( raf );
8385 			} else {
8386 				timerId = setInterval( fx.tick, fx.interval );
8387 			}
8388 		}
8389 	},
8390 
8391 	// Simple 'show' function
8392 	show: function() {
8393 		// Remember where we started, so that we can go back to it later
8394 		this.options.orig[this.prop] = jQuery.style( this.elem, this.prop );
8395 		this.options.show = true;
8396 
8397 		// Begin the animation
8398 		// Make sure that we start at a small width/height to avoid any
8399 		// flash of content
8400 		this.custom(this.prop === "width" || this.prop === "height" ? 1 : 0, this.cur());
8401 
8402 		// Start by showing the element
8403 		jQuery( this.elem ).show();
8404 	},
8405 
8406 	// Simple 'hide' function
8407 	hide: function() {
8408 		// Remember where we started, so that we can go back to it later
8409 		this.options.orig[this.prop] = jQuery.style( this.elem, this.prop );
8410 		this.options.hide = true;
8411 
8412 		// Begin the animation
8413 		this.custom(this.cur(), 0);
8414 	},
8415 
8416 	// Each step of an animation
8417 	step: function( gotoEnd ) {
8418 		var t = fxNow || createFxNow(),
8419 			done = true,
8420 			elem = this.elem,
8421 			options = this.options,
8422 			i, n;
8423 
8424 		if ( gotoEnd || t >= options.duration + this.startTime ) {
8425 			this.now = this.end;
8426 			this.pos = this.state = 1;
8427 			this.update();
8428 
8429 			options.animatedProperties[ this.prop ] = true;
8430 
8431 			for ( i in options.animatedProperties ) {
8432 				if ( options.animatedProperties[i] !== true ) {
8433 					done = false;
8434 				}
8435 			}
8436 
8437 			if ( done ) {
8438 				// Reset the overflow
8439 				if ( options.overflow != null && !jQuery.support.shrinkWrapBlocks ) {
8440 
8441 					jQuery.each( [ "", "X", "Y" ], function (index, value) {
8442 						elem.style[ "overflow" + value ] = options.overflow[index];
8443 					});
8444 				}
8445 
8446 				// Hide the element if the "hide" operation was done
8447 				if ( options.hide ) {
8448 					jQuery(elem).hide();
8449 				}
8450 
8451 				// Reset the properties, if the item has been hidden or shown
8452 				if ( options.hide || options.show ) {
8453 					for ( var p in options.animatedProperties ) {
8454 						jQuery.style( elem, p, options.orig[p] );
8455 					}
8456 				}
8457 
8458 				// Execute the complete function
8459 				options.complete.call( elem );
8460 			}
8461 
8462 			return false;
8463 
8464 		} else {
8465 			// classical easing cannot be used with an Infinity duration
8466 			if ( options.duration == Infinity ) {
8467 				this.now = t;
8468 			} else {
8469 				n = t - this.startTime;
8470 				this.state = n / options.duration;
8471 
8472 				// Perform the easing function, defaults to swing
8473 				this.pos = jQuery.easing[ options.animatedProperties[ this.prop ] ]( this.state, n, 0, 1, options.duration );
8474 				this.now = this.start + ((this.end - this.start) * this.pos);
8475 			}
8476 			// Perform the next step of the animation
8477 			this.update();
8478 		}
8479 
8480 		return true;
8481 	}
8482 };

8484 jQuery.extend( jQuery.fx, {
8485 	tick: function() {
8486 		for ( var timers = jQuery.timers, i = 0 ; i < timers.length ; ++i ) {
8487 			if ( !timers[i]() ) {
8488 				timers.splice(i--, 1);
8489 			}
8490 		}
8491 
8492 		if ( !timers.length ) {
8493 			jQuery.fx.stop();
8494 		}
8495 	},
8496 
8497 	interval: 13,
8498 
8499 	stop: function() {
8500 		clearInterval( timerId );
8501 		timerId = null;
8502 	},
8503 
8504 	speeds: {
8505 		slow: 600,
8506 		fast: 200,
8507 		// Default speed
8508 		_default: 400
8509 	},
8510 
8511 	step: {
8512 		opacity: function( fx ) {
8513 			jQuery.style( fx.elem, "opacity", fx.now );
8514 		},
8515 
8516 		_default: function( fx ) {
8517 			if ( fx.elem.style && fx.elem.style[ fx.prop ] != null ) {
8518 				fx.elem.style[ fx.prop ] = (fx.prop === "width" || fx.prop === "height" ? Math.max(0, fx.now) : fx.now) + fx.unit;
8519 			} else {
8520 				fx.elem[ fx.prop ] = fx.now;
8521 			}
8522 		}
8523 	}

8534 // Try to restore the default display value of an element
8535 function defaultDisplay( nodeName ) {
8536 
8537 	if ( !elemdisplay[ nodeName ] ) {
8538 
8539 		var elem = jQuery( "<" + nodeName + ">" ).appendTo( "body" ),
8540 			display = elem.css( "display" );
8541 
8542 		elem.remove();
8543 
8544 		// If the simple way fails,
8545 		// get element's real default display by attaching it to a temp iframe
8546 		if ( display === "none" || display === "" ) {
8547 			// No iframe to use yet, so create it
8548 			if ( !iframe ) {
8549 				iframe = document.createElement( "iframe" );
8550 				iframe.frameBorder = iframe.width = iframe.height = 0;
8551 			}
8552 
8553 			document.body.appendChild( iframe );
8554 
8555 			// Create a cacheable copy of the iframe document on first call.
8556 			// IE and Opera will allow us to reuse the iframeDoc without re-writing the fake html
8557 			// document to it, Webkit & Firefox won't allow reusing the iframe document
8558 			if ( !iframeDoc || !iframe.createElement ) {
8559 				iframeDoc = ( iframe.contentWindow || iframe.contentDocument ).document;
8560 				iframeDoc.write( "<!doctype><html><body></body></html>" );
8561 			}
8562 
8563 			elem = iframeDoc.createElement( nodeName );
8564 
8565 			iframeDoc.body.appendChild( elem );
8566 
8567 			display = jQuery.css( elem, "display" );
8568 
8569 			document.body.removeChild( iframe );
8570 		}
8571 
8572 		// Store the correct default display
8573 		elemdisplay[ nodeName ] = display;
8574 	}
8575 
8576 	return elemdisplay[ nodeName ];
8577 }

8582 var rtable = /^t(?:able|d|h)$/i,
8583 	rroot = /^(?:body|html)$/i;
8584 
8585 if ( "getBoundingClientRect" in document.documentElement ) {
8586 	jQuery.fn.offset = function( options ) {
8587 		var elem = this[0], box;
8588 
8589 		if ( options ) {
8590 			return this.each(function( i ) {
8591 				jQuery.offset.setOffset( this, options, i );
8592 			});
8593 		}
8594 
8595 		if ( !elem || !elem.ownerDocument ) {
8596 			return null;
8597 		}
8598 
8599 		if ( elem === elem.ownerDocument.body ) {
8600 			return jQuery.offset.bodyOffset( elem );
8601 		}
8602 
8603 		try {
8604 			box = elem.getBoundingClientRect();
8605 		} catch(e) {}
8606 
8607 		var doc = elem.ownerDocument,
8608 			docElem = doc.documentElement;
8609 
8610 		// Make sure we're not dealing with a disconnected DOM node
8611 		if ( !box || !jQuery.contains( docElem, elem ) ) {
8612 			return box ? { top: box.top, left: box.left } : { top: 0, left: 0 };
8613 		}
8614 
8615 		var body = doc.body,
8616 			win = getWindow(doc),
8617 			clientTop  = docElem.clientTop  || body.clientTop  || 0,
8618 			clientLeft = docElem.clientLeft || body.clientLeft || 0,
8619 			scrollTop  = win.pageYOffset || jQuery.support.boxModel && docElem.scrollTop  || body.scrollTop,
8620 			scrollLeft = win.pageXOffset || jQuery.support.boxModel && docElem.scrollLeft || body.scrollLeft,
8621 			top  = box.top  + scrollTop  - clientTop,
8622 			left = box.left + scrollLeft - clientLeft;
8623 
8624 		return { top: top, left: left };
8625 	};
8626 
8627 } else {
8628 	jQuery.fn.offset = function( options ) {
8629 		var elem = this[0];
8630 
8631 		if ( options ) {
8632 			return this.each(function( i ) {
8633 				jQuery.offset.setOffset( this, options, i );
8634 			});
8635 		}
8636 
8637 		if ( !elem || !elem.ownerDocument ) {
8638 			return null;
8639 		}
8640 
8641 		if ( elem === elem.ownerDocument.body ) {
8642 			return jQuery.offset.bodyOffset( elem );
8643 		}
8644 
8645 		jQuery.offset.initialize();
8646 
8647 		var computedStyle,
8648 			offsetParent = elem.offsetParent,
8649 			prevOffsetParent = elem,
8650 			doc = elem.ownerDocument,
8651 			docElem = doc.documentElement,
8652 			body = doc.body,
8653 			defaultView = doc.defaultView,
8654 			prevComputedStyle = defaultView ? defaultView.getComputedStyle( elem, null ) : elem.currentStyle,
8655 			top = elem.offsetTop,
8656 			left = elem.offsetLeft;
8657 
8658 		while ( (elem = elem.parentNode) && elem !== body && elem !== docElem ) {
8659 			if ( jQuery.offset.supportsFixedPosition && prevComputedStyle.position === "fixed" ) {
8660 				break;
8661 			}
8662 
8663 			computedStyle = defaultView ? defaultView.getComputedStyle(elem, null) : elem.currentStyle;
8664 			top  -= elem.scrollTop;
8665 			left -= elem.scrollLeft;
8666 
8667 			if ( elem === offsetParent ) {
8668 				top  += elem.offsetTop;
8669 				left += elem.offsetLeft;
8670 
8671 				if ( jQuery.offset.doesNotAddBorder && !(jQuery.offset.doesAddBorderForTableAndCells && rtable.test(elem.nodeName)) ) {
8672 					top  += parseFloat( computedStyle.borderTopWidth  ) || 0;
8673 					left += parseFloat( computedStyle.borderLeftWidth ) || 0;
8674 				}
8675 
8676 				prevOffsetParent = offsetParent;
8677 				offsetParent = elem.offsetParent;
8678 			}
8679 
8680 			if ( jQuery.offset.subtractsBorderForOverflowNotVisible && computedStyle.overflow !== "visible" ) {
8681 				top  += parseFloat( computedStyle.borderTopWidth  ) || 0;
8682 				left += parseFloat( computedStyle.borderLeftWidth ) || 0;
8683 			}
8684 
8685 			prevComputedStyle = computedStyle;
8686 		}
8687 
8688 		if ( prevComputedStyle.position === "relative" || prevComputedStyle.position === "static" ) {
8689 			top  += body.offsetTop;
8690 			left += body.offsetLeft;
8691 		}
8692 
8693 		if ( jQuery.offset.supportsFixedPosition && prevComputedStyle.position === "fixed" ) {
8694 			top  += Math.max( docElem.scrollTop, body.scrollTop );
8695 			left += Math.max( docElem.scrollLeft, body.scrollLeft );
8696 		}
8697 
8698 		return { top: top, left: left };
8699 	};
8700 }

8702 jQuery.offset = {
8703 	initialize: function() {
8704 		var body = document.body, container = document.createElement("div"), innerDiv, checkDiv, table, td, bodyMarginTop = parseFloat( jQuery.css(body, "marginTop") ) || 0,
8705 			html = "<div style='position:absolute;top:0;left:0;margin:0;border:5px solid #000;padding:0;width:1px;height:1px;'><div></div></div><table style='position:absolute;top:0;left:0;margin:0;border:5px solid #000;padding:0;width:1px;height:1px;' cellpadding='0' cellspacing='0'><tr><td></td></tr></table>";
8706 
8707 		jQuery.extend( container.style, { position: "absolute", top: 0, left: 0, margin: 0, border: 0, width: "1px", height: "1px", visibility: "hidden" } );
8708 
8709 		container.innerHTML = html;
8710 		body.insertBefore( container, body.firstChild );
8711 		innerDiv = container.firstChild;
8712 		checkDiv = innerDiv.firstChild;
8713 		td = innerDiv.nextSibling.firstChild.firstChild;
8714 
8715 		this.doesNotAddBorder = (checkDiv.offsetTop !== 5);
8716 		this.doesAddBorderForTableAndCells = (td.offsetTop === 5);
8717 
8718 		checkDiv.style.position = "fixed";
8719 		checkDiv.style.top = "20px";
8720 
8721 		// safari subtracts parent border width here which is 5px
8722 		this.supportsFixedPosition = (checkDiv.offsetTop === 20 || checkDiv.offsetTop === 15);
8723 		checkDiv.style.position = checkDiv.style.top = "";
8724 
8725 		innerDiv.style.overflow = "hidden";
8726 		innerDiv.style.position = "relative";
8727 
8728 		this.subtractsBorderForOverflowNotVisible = (checkDiv.offsetTop === -5);
8729 
8730 		this.doesNotIncludeMarginInBodyOffset = (body.offsetTop !== bodyMarginTop);
8731 
8732 		body.removeChild( container );
8733 		jQuery.offset.initialize = jQuery.noop;
8734 	},
8735 
8736 	bodyOffset: function( body ) {
8737 		var top = body.offsetTop,
8738 			left = body.offsetLeft;
8739 
8740 		jQuery.offset.initialize();
8741 
8742 		if ( jQuery.offset.doesNotIncludeMarginInBodyOffset ) {
8743 			top  += parseFloat( jQuery.css(body, "marginTop") ) || 0;
8744 			left += parseFloat( jQuery.css(body, "marginLeft") ) || 0;
8745 		}
8746 
8747 		return { top: top, left: left };
8748 	},
8749 
8750 	setOffset: function( elem, options, i ) {
8751 		var position = jQuery.css( elem, "position" );
8752 
8753 		// set position first, in-case top/left are set even on static elem
8754 		if ( position === "static" ) {
8755 			elem.style.position = "relative";
8756 		}
8757 
8758 		var curElem = jQuery( elem ),
8759 			curOffset = curElem.offset(),
8760 			curCSSTop = jQuery.css( elem, "top" ),
8761 			curCSSLeft = jQuery.css( elem, "left" ),
8762 			calculatePosition = (position === "absolute" || position === "fixed") && jQuery.inArray("auto", [curCSSTop, curCSSLeft]) > -1,
8763 			props = {}, curPosition = {}, curTop, curLeft;
8764 
8765 		// need to be able to calculate position if either top or left is auto and position is either absolute or fixed
8766 		if ( calculatePosition ) {
8767 			curPosition = curElem.position();
8768 			curTop = curPosition.top;
8769 			curLeft = curPosition.left;
8770 		} else {
8771 			curTop = parseFloat( curCSSTop ) || 0;
8772 			curLeft = parseFloat( curCSSLeft ) || 0;
8773 		}
8774 
8775 		if ( jQuery.isFunction( options ) ) {
8776 			options = options.call( elem, i, curOffset );
8777 		}
8778 
8779 		if (options.top != null) {
8780 			props.top = (options.top - curOffset.top) + curTop;
8781 		}
8782 		if (options.left != null) {
8783 			props.left = (options.left - curOffset.left) + curLeft;
8784 		}
8785 
8786 		if ( "using" in options ) {
8787 			options.using.call( elem, props );
8788 		} else {
8789 			curElem.css( props );
8790 		}
8791 	}
8792 };

8795 jQuery.fn.extend({
8796 	position: function() {
8797 		if ( !this[0] ) {
8798 			return null;
8799 		}
8800 
8801 		var elem = this[0],
8802 
8803 		// Get *real* offsetParent
8804 		offsetParent = this.offsetParent(),
8805 
8806 		// Get correct offsets
8807 		offset       = this.offset(),
8808 		parentOffset = rroot.test(offsetParent[0].nodeName) ? { top: 0, left: 0 } : offsetParent.offset();
8809 
8810 		// Subtract element margins
8811 		// note: when an element has margin: auto the offsetLeft and marginLeft
8812 		// are the same in Safari causing offset.left to incorrectly be 0
8813 		offset.top  -= parseFloat( jQuery.css(elem, "marginTop") ) || 0;
8814 		offset.left -= parseFloat( jQuery.css(elem, "marginLeft") ) || 0;
8815 
8816 		// Add offsetParent borders
8817 		parentOffset.top  += parseFloat( jQuery.css(offsetParent[0], "borderTopWidth") ) || 0;
8818 		parentOffset.left += parseFloat( jQuery.css(offsetParent[0], "borderLeftWidth") ) || 0;
8819 
8820 		// Subtract the two offsets
8821 		return {
8822 			top:  offset.top  - parentOffset.top,
8823 			left: offset.left - parentOffset.left
8824 		};
8825 	},
8826 
8827 	offsetParent: function() {
8828 		return this.map(function() {
8829 			var offsetParent = this.offsetParent || document.body;
8830 			while ( offsetParent && (!rroot.test(offsetParent.nodeName) && jQuery.css(offsetParent, "position") === "static") ) {
8831 				offsetParent = offsetParent.offsetParent;
8832 			}
8833 			return offsetParent;
8834 		});
8835 	}

8839 // Create scrollLeft and scrollTop methods
8840 jQuery.each( ["Left", "Top"], function( i, name ) {
8841 	var method = "scroll" + name;
8842 
8843 	jQuery.fn[ method ] = function( val ) {
8844 		var elem, win;
8845 
8846 		if ( val === undefined ) {
8847 			elem = this[ 0 ];
8848 
8849 			if ( !elem ) {
8850 				return null;
8851 			}
8852 
8853 			win = getWindow( elem );
8854 
8855 			// Return the scroll offset
8856 			return win ? ("pageXOffset" in win) ? win[ i ? "pageYOffset" : "pageXOffset" ] :
8857 				jQuery.support.boxModel && win.document.documentElement[ method ] ||
8858 					win.document.body[ method ] :
8859 				elem[ method ];
8860 		}
8861 
8862 		// Set the scroll offset
8863 8864 		return this.each(function() {
8865 			win = getWindow( this );
8866 
8867 			if ( win ) {
8868 				win.scrollTo(
8869 					!i ? val : jQuery( win ).scrollLeft(),
8870 					 i ? val : jQuery( win ).scrollTop()
8871 				);
8872 
8873 			} else {
8874 				this[ method ] = val;
8875 			}
8876 		});
8877 	};
8878 });

8880 function getWindow( elem ) {
8881 	return jQuery.isWindow( elem ) ?
8882 		elem :
8883 		elem.nodeType === 9 ?
8884 			elem.defaultView || elem.parentWindow :
8885 			false;
8886 }

8891 // Create innerHeight, innerWidth, outerHeight and outerWidth methods
8892 jQuery.each([ "Height", "Width" ], function( i, name ) {
8893 
8894 	var type = name.toLowerCase();
8895 
8896 	// innerHeight and innerWidth
8897 	jQuery.fn["inner" + name] = function() {
8898 		return this[0] ?
8899 			parseFloat( jQuery.css( this[0], type, "padding" ) ) :
8900 			null;
8901 	};
8902 
8903 	// outerHeight and outerWidth
8904 	jQuery.fn["outer" + name] = function( margin ) {
8905 		return this[0] ?
8906 			parseFloat( jQuery.css( this[0], type, margin ? "margin" : "border" ) ) :
8907 			null;
8908 	};
8909 
8910 	jQuery.fn[ type ] = function( size ) {
8911 		// Get window width or height
8912 		var elem = this[0];
8913 		if ( !elem ) {
8914 			return size == null ? null : this;
8915 		}
8916 
8917 		if ( jQuery.isFunction( size ) ) {
8918 			return this.each(function( i ) {
8919 				var self = jQuery( this );
8920 				self[ type ]( size.call( this, i, self[ type ]() ) );
8921 			});
8922 		}
8923 
8924 		if ( jQuery.isWindow( elem ) ) {
8925 			// Everyone else use document.documentElement or document.body depending on Quirks vs Standards mode
8926 			// 3rd condition allows Nokia support, as it supports the docElem prop but not CSS1Compat
8927 			var docElemProp = elem.document.documentElement[ "client" + name ];
8928 			return elem.document.compatMode === "CSS1Compat" && docElemProp ||
8929 				elem.document.body[ "client" + name ] || docElemProp;
8930 
8931 		// Get document width or height
8932 		} else if ( elem.nodeType === 9 ) {
8933 			// Either scroll[Width/Height] or offset[Width/Height], whichever is greater
8934 			return Math.max(
8935 				elem.documentElement["client" + name],
8936 				elem.body["scroll" + name], elem.documentElement["scroll" + name],
8937 				elem.body["offset" + name], elem.documentElement["offset" + name]
8938 			);
8939 
8940 		// Get or set width or height on the element
8941 		} else if ( size === undefined ) {
8942 			var orig = jQuery.css( elem, type ),
8943 				ret = parseFloat( orig );
8944 
8945 			return jQuery.isNaN( ret ) ? orig : ret;
8946 
8947 		// Set the width or height on the element (default to pixels if value is unitless)
8948 		} else {
8949 			return this.css( type, typeof size === "string" ? size : size + "px" );
8950 		}
8951 	};
8952 
8953 });
